18void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateHeader(const std::string& source)
19{
20 std::string code = R"CODE(//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
21// Automatically generated by the Fast Binary Encoding compiler, do not modify!
22// https://github.com/chronoxor/FastBinaryEncoding
23// Source: _INPUT_
24// FBE version: _VERSION_
25//------------------------------------------------------------------------------
26)CODE";
27
28 // Prepare code template
29 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_INPUT_"), source);
30 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_VERSION_"), version);
31 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
32
33 Write(code);
34}

41void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateBig(const CppCommon::Path& path)
42{
43 // Generate the common file
44 CppCommon::Path common = path / "big.js";
45 WriteBegin();
46
47 // Generate common header
48 GenerateHeader("FBE");
49
50 std::string code = R"CODE(
51/* eslint-disable */
52
53/*
54 * big.js v5.1.2
55 * A small, fast, easy-to-use library for arbitrary-precision decimal arithmetic.
56 * Copyright (c) 2017 Michael Mclaughlin <M8ch88l@gmail.com>
57 * https://github.com/MikeMcl/big.js/LICENCE
58 */
59;(function (GLOBAL) {
60 'use strict';
61 var Big,
62
63
64/************************************** EDITABLE DEFAULTS *****************************************/
65
66
67 // The default values below must be integers within the stated ranges.
68
69 /*
70 * The maximum number of decimal places (DP) of the results of operations involving division:
71 * div and sqrt, and pow with negative exponents.
72 */
73 DP = 20, // 0 to MAX_DP
74
75 /*
76 * The rounding mode (RM) used when rounding to the above decimal places.
77 *
78 * 0 Towards zero (i.e. truncate, no rounding). (ROUND_DOWN)
79 * 1 To nearest neighbour. If equidistant, round up. (ROUND_HALF_UP)
80 * 2 To nearest neighbour. If equidistant, to even. (ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
81 * 3 Away from zero. (ROUND_UP)
82 */
83 RM = 1, // 0, 1, 2 or 3
84
85 // The maximum value of DP and Big.DP.
86 MAX_DP = 1E6, // 0 to 1000000
87
88 // The maximum magnitude of the exponent argument to the pow method.
89 MAX_POWER = 1E6, // 1 to 1000000
90
91 /*
92 * The negative exponent (NE) at and beneath which toString returns exponential notation.
93 * (JavaScript numbers: -7)
94 * -1000000 is the minimum recommended exponent value of a Big.
95 */
96 NE = -7, // 0 to -1000000
97
98 /*
99 * The positive exponent (PE) at and above which toString returns exponential notation.
100 * (JavaScript numbers: 21)
101 * 1000000 is the maximum recommended exponent value of a Big.
102 * (This limit is not enforced or checked.)
103 */
104 PE = 21, // 0 to 1000000
105
106
107/**************************************************************************************************/
108)CODE";
109
110 // Prepare code template
111 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
112
113 Write(code);
114
115 code = R"CODE(
116
117 // Error messages.
118 NAME = '[big.js] ',
119 INVALID = NAME + 'Invalid ',
120 INVALID_DP = INVALID + 'decimal places',
121 INVALID_RM = INVALID + 'rounding mode',
122 DIV_BY_ZERO = NAME + 'Division by zero',
123
124 // The shared prototype object.
125 P = {},
126 UNDEFINED = void 0,
127 NUMERIC = /^-?(\d+(\.\d*)?|\.\d+)(e[+-]?\d+)?$/i;
128
129
130 /*
131 * Create and return a Big constructor.
132 *
133 */
134 function _Big_() {
135
136 /*
137 * The Big constructor and exported function.
138 * Create and return a new instance of a Big number object.
139 *
140 * n {number|string|Big} A numeric value.
141 */
142 function Big(n) {
143 var x = this;
144
145 // Enable constructor usage without new.
146 if (!(x instanceof Big)) return n === UNDEFINED ? _Big_() : new Big(n);
147
148 // Duplicate.
149 if (n instanceof Big) {
150 x.s = n.s;
151 x.e = n.e;
152 x.c = n.c.slice();
153 } else {
154 parse(x, n);
155 }
156
157 /*
158 * Retain a reference to this Big constructor, and shadow Big.prototype.constructor which
159 * points to Object.
160 */
161 x.constructor = Big;
162 }
163
164 Big.prototype = P;
165 Big.DP = DP;
166 Big.RM = RM;
167 Big.NE = NE;
168 Big.PE = PE;
169 Big.version = '5.0.2';
170
171 return Big;
172 }
173
174
175 /*
176 * Parse the number or string value passed to a Big constructor.
177 *
178 * x {Big} A Big number instance.
179 * n {number|string} A numeric value.
180 */
181 function parse(x, n) {
182 var e, i, nl;
183
184 // Minus zero?
185 if (n === 0 && 1 / n < 0) n = '-0';
186 else if (!NUMERIC.test(n += '')) throw Error(INVALID + 'number');
187
188 // Determine sign.
189 x.s = n.charAt(0) == '-' ? (n = n.slice(1), -1) : 1;
190
191 // Decimal point?
192 if ((e = n.indexOf('.')) > -1) n = n.replace('.', '');
193
194 // Exponential form?
195 if ((i = n.search(/e/i)) > 0) {
196
197 // Determine exponent.
198 if (e < 0) e = i;
199 e += +n.slice(i + 1);
200 n = n.substring(0, i);
201 } else if (e < 0) {
202
203 // Integer.
204 e = n.length;
205 }
206
207 nl = n.length;
208
209 // Determine leading zeros.
210 for (i = 0; i < nl && n.charAt(i) == '0';) ++i;
211
212 if (i == nl) {
213
214 // Zero.
215 x.c = [x.e = 0];
216 } else {
217
218 // Determine trailing zeros.
219 for (; nl > 0 && n.charAt(--nl) == '0';);
220 x.e = e - i - 1;
221 x.c = [];
222
223 // Convert string to array of digits without leading/trailing zeros.
224 for (e = 0; i <= nl;) x.c[e++] = +n.charAt(i++);
225 }
226
227 return x;
228 }
229
230
231 /*
232 * Round Big x to a maximum of dp decimal places using rounding mode rm.
233 * Called by stringify, P.div, P.round and P.sqrt.
234 *
235 * x {Big} The Big to round.
236 * dp {number} Integer, 0 to MAX_DP inclusive.
237 * rm {number} 0, 1, 2 or 3 (DOWN, HALF_UP, HALF_EVEN, UP)
238 * [more] {boolean} Whether the result of division was truncated.
239 */
240 function round(x, dp, rm, more) {
241 var xc = x.c,
242 i = x.e + dp + 1;
243
244 if (i < xc.length) {
245 if (rm === 1) {
246
247 // xc[i] is the digit after the digit that may be rounded up.
248 more = xc[i] >= 5;
249 } else if (rm === 2) {
250 more = xc[i] > 5 || xc[i] == 5 &&
251 (more || i < 0 || xc[i + 1] !== UNDEFINED || xc[i - 1] & 1);
252 } else if (rm === 3) {
253 more = more || xc[i] !== UNDEFINED || i < 0;
254 } else {
255 more = false;
256 if (rm !== 0) throw Error(INVALID_RM);
257 }
258
259 if (i < 1) {
260 xc.length = 1;
261
262 if (more) {
263
264 // 1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.0001 etc.
265 x.e = -dp;
266 xc[0] = 1;
267 } else {
268
269 // Zero.
270 xc[0] = x.e = 0;
271 }
272 } else {
273
274 // Remove any digits after the required decimal places.
275 xc.length = i--;
276
277 // Round up?
278 if (more) {
279
280 // Rounding up may mean the previous digit has to be rounded up.
281 for (; ++xc[i] > 9;) {
282 xc[i] = 0;
283 if (!i--) {
284 ++x.e;
285 xc.unshift(1);
286 }
287 }
288 }
289
290 // Remove trailing zeros.
291 for (i = xc.length; !xc[--i];) xc.pop();
292 }
293 } else if (rm < 0 || rm > 3 || rm !== ~~rm) {
294 throw Error(INVALID_RM);
295 }
296
297 return x;
298 }
299
300
301 /*
302 * Return a string representing the value of Big x in normal or exponential notation.
303 * Handles P.toExponential, P.toFixed, P.toJSON, P.toPrecision, P.toString and P.valueOf.
304 *
305 * x {Big}
306 * id? {number} Caller id.
307 * 1 toExponential
308 * 2 toFixed
309 * 3 toPrecision
310 * 4 valueOf
311 * n? {number|undefined} Caller's argument.
312 * k? {number|undefined}
313 */
314 function stringify(x, id, n, k) {
315 var e, s,
316 Big = x.constructor,
317 z = !x.c[0];
318
319 if (n !== UNDEFINED) {
320 if (n !== ~~n || n < (id == 3) || n > MAX_DP) {
321 throw Error(id == 3 ? INVALID + 'precision' : INVALID_DP);
322 }
323
324 x = new Big(x);
325
326 // The index of the digit that may be rounded up.
327 n = k - x.e;
328
329 // Round?
330 if (x.c.length > ++k) round(x, n, Big.RM);
331
332 // toFixed: recalculate k as x.e may have changed if value rounded up.
333 if (id == 2) k = x.e + n + 1;
334
335 // Append zeros?
336 for (; x.c.length < k;) x.c.push(0);
337 }
338
339 e = x.e;
340 s = x.c.join('');
341 n = s.length;
342
343 // Exponential notation?
344 if (id != 2 && (id == 1 || id == 3 && k <= e || e <= Big.NE || e >= Big.PE)) {
345 s = s.charAt(0) + (n > 1 ? '.' + s.slice(1) : '') + (e < 0 ? 'e' : 'e+') + e;
346
347 // Normal notation.
348 } else if (e < 0) {
349 for (; ++e;) s = '0' + s;
350 s = '0.' + s;
351 } else if (e > 0) {
352 if (++e > n) for (e -= n; e--;) s += '0';
353 else if (e < n) s = s.slice(0, e) + '.' + s.slice(e);
354 } else if (n > 1) {
355 s = s.charAt(0) + '.' + s.slice(1);
356 }
357
358 return x.s < 0 && (!z || id == 4) ? '-' + s : s;
359 }
360)CODE";
361
362 // Prepare code template
363 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
364
365 Write(code);
366
367 code = R"CODE(
368
369 // Prototype/instance methods
370
371
372 /*
373 * Return a new Big whose value is the absolute value of this Big.
374 */
375 P.abs = function () {
376 var x = new this.constructor(this);
377 x.s = 1;
378 return x;
379 };
380
381
382 /*
383 * Return 1 if the value of this Big is greater than the value of Big y,
384 * -1 if the value of this Big is less than the value of Big y, or
385 * 0 if they have the same value.
386 */
387 P.cmp = function (y) {
388 var isneg,
389 x = this,
390 xc = x.c,
391 yc = (y = new x.constructor(y)).c,
392 i = x.s,
393 j = y.s,
394 k = x.e,
395 l = y.e;
396
397 // Either zero?
398 if (!xc[0] || !yc[0]) return !xc[0] ? !yc[0] ? 0 : -j : i;
399
400 // Signs differ?
401 if (i != j) return i;
402
403 isneg = i < 0;
404
405 // Compare exponents.
406 if (k != l) return k > l ^ isneg ? 1 : -1;
407
408 j = (k = xc.length) < (l = yc.length) ? k : l;
409
410 // Compare digit by digit.
411 for (i = -1; ++i < j;) {
412 if (xc[i] != yc[i]) return xc[i] > yc[i] ^ isneg ? 1 : -1;
413 }
414
415 // Compare lengths.
416 return k == l ? 0 : k > l ^ isneg ? 1 : -1;
417 };
418
419
420 /*
421 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big divided by the value of Big y, rounded,
422 * if necessary, to a maximum of Big.DP decimal places using rounding mode Big.RM.
423 */
424 P.div = function (y) {
425 var x = this,
426 Big = x.constructor,
427 a = x.c, // dividend
428 b = (y = new Big(y)).c, // divisor
429 k = x.s == y.s ? 1 : -1,
430 dp = Big.DP;
431
432 if (dp !== ~~dp || dp < 0 || dp > MAX_DP) throw Error(INVALID_DP);
433
434 // Divisor is zero?
435 if (!b[0]) throw Error(DIV_BY_ZERO);
436
437 // Dividend is 0? Return +-0.
438 if (!a[0]) return new Big(k * 0);
439
440 var bl, bt, n, cmp, ri,
441 bz = b.slice(),
442 ai = bl = b.length,
443 al = a.length,
444 r = a.slice(0, bl), // remainder
445 rl = r.length,
446 q = y, // quotient
447 qc = q.c = [],
448 qi = 0,
449 d = dp + (q.e = x.e - y.e) + 1; // number of digits of the result
450
451 q.s = k;
452 k = d < 0 ? 0 : d;
453
454 // Create version of divisor with leading zero.
455 bz.unshift(0);
456
457 // Add zeros to make remainder as long as divisor.
458 for (; rl++ < bl;) r.push(0);
459
460 do {
461
462 // n is how many times the divisor goes into current remainder.
463 for (n = 0; n < 10; n++) {
464
465 // Compare divisor and remainder.
466 if (bl != (rl = r.length)) {
467 cmp = bl > rl ? 1 : -1;
468 } else {
469 for (ri = -1, cmp = 0; ++ri < bl;) {
470 if (b[ri] != r[ri]) {
471 cmp = b[ri] > r[ri] ? 1 : -1;
472 break;
473 }
474 }
475 }
476
477 // If divisor < remainder, subtract divisor from remainder.
478 if (cmp < 0) {
479
480 // Remainder can't be more than 1 digit longer than divisor.
481 // Equalise lengths using divisor with extra leading zero?
482 for (bt = rl == bl ? b : bz; rl;) {
483 if (r[--rl] < bt[rl]) {
484 ri = rl;
485 for (; ri && !r[--ri];) r[ri] = 9;
486 --r[ri];
487 r[rl] += 10;
488 }
489 r[rl] -= bt[rl];
490 }
491
492 for (; !r[0];) r.shift();
493 } else {
494 break;
495 }
496 }
497
498 // Add the digit n to the result array.
499 qc[qi++] = cmp ? n : ++n;
500
501 // Update the remainder.
502 if (r[0] && cmp) r[rl] = a[ai] || 0;
503 else r = [a[ai]];
504
505 } while ((ai++ < al || r[0] !== UNDEFINED) && k--);
506
507 // Leading zero? Do not remove if result is simply zero (qi == 1).
508 if (!qc[0] && qi != 1) {
509
510 // There can't be more than one zero.
511 qc.shift();
512 q.e--;
513 }
514
515 // Round?
516 if (qi > d) round(q, dp, Big.RM, r[0] !== UNDEFINED);
517
518 return q;
519 };
520

522 /*
523 * Return true if the value of this Big is equal to the value of Big y, otherwise return false.
524 */
525 P.eq = function (y) {
526 return !this.cmp(y);
527 };

531 * Return true if the value of this Big is greater than the value of Big y, otherwise return
532 * false.
533 */
534 P.gt = function (y) {
535 return this.cmp(y) > 0;
536 };
537
538
539 /*
540 * Return true if the value of this Big is greater than or equal to the value of Big y, otherwise
541 * return false.
542 */
543 P.gte = function (y) {
544 return this.cmp(y) > -1;
545 };
546
547
548 /*
549 * Return true if the value of this Big is less than the value of Big y, otherwise return false.
550 */
551 P.lt = function (y) {
552 return this.cmp(y) < 0;
553 };
554
555
556 /*
557 * Return true if the value of this Big is less than or equal to the value of Big y, otherwise
558 * return false.
559 */
560 P.lte = function (y) {
561 return this.cmp(y) < 1;
562 };
563
564
565 /*
566 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big minus the value of Big y.
567 */
568 P.minus = P.sub = function (y) {
569 var i, j, t, xlty,
570 x = this,
571 Big = x.constructor,
572 a = x.s,
573 b = (y = new Big(y)).s;
574
575 // Signs differ?
576 if (a != b) {
577 y.s = -b;
578 return x.plus(y);
579 }
580
581 var xc = x.c.slice(),
582 xe = x.e,
583 yc = y.c,
584 ye = y.e;
585
586 // Either zero?
587 if (!xc[0] || !yc[0]) {
588
589 // y is non-zero? x is non-zero? Or both are zero.
590 return yc[0] ? (y.s = -b, y) : new Big(xc[0] ? x : 0);
591 }
592
593 // Determine which is the bigger number. Prepend zeros to equalise exponents.
594 if (a = xe - ye) {
595
596 if (xlty = a < 0) {
597 a = -a;
598 t = xc;
599 } else {
600 ye = xe;
601 t = yc;
602 }
603
604 t.reverse();
605 for (b = a; b--;) t.push(0);
606 t.reverse();
607 } else {
608
609 // Exponents equal. Check digit by digit.
610 j = ((xlty = xc.length < yc.length) ? xc : yc).length;
611
612 for (a = b = 0; b < j; b++) {
613 if (xc[b] != yc[b]) {
614 xlty = xc[b] < yc[b];
615 break;
616 }
617 }
618 }
619
620 // x < y? Point xc to the array of the bigger number.
621 if (xlty) {
622 t = xc;
623 xc = yc;
624 yc = t;
625 y.s = -y.s;
626 }
627
628 /*
629 * Append zeros to xc if shorter. No need to add zeros to yc if shorter as subtraction only
630 * needs to start at yc.length.
631 */
632 if ((b = (j = yc.length) - (i = xc.length)) > 0) for (; b--;) xc[i++] = 0;
633
634 // Subtract yc from xc.
635 for (b = i; j > a;) {
636 if (xc[--j] < yc[j]) {
637 for (i = j; i && !xc[--i];) xc[i] = 9;
638 --xc[i];
639 xc[j] += 10;
640 }
641
642 xc[j] -= yc[j];
643 }
644
645 // Remove trailing zeros.
646 for (; xc[--b] === 0;) xc.pop();
647
648 // Remove leading zeros and adjust exponent accordingly.
649 for (; xc[0] === 0;) {
650 xc.shift();
651 --ye;
652 }
653
654 if (!xc[0]) {
655
656 // n - n = +0
657 y.s = 1;
658
659 // Result must be zero.
660 xc = [ye = 0];
661 }
662
663 y.c = xc;
664 y.e = ye;
665
666 return y;
667 };
668
669
670 /*
671 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big modulo the value of Big y.
672 */
673 P.mod = function (y) {
674 var ygtx,
675 x = this,
676 Big = x.constructor,
677 a = x.s,
678 b = (y = new Big(y)).s;
679
680 if (!y.c[0]) throw Error(DIV_BY_ZERO);
681
682 x.s = y.s = 1;
683 ygtx = y.cmp(x) == 1;
684 x.s = a;
685 y.s = b;
686
687 if (ygtx) return new Big(x);
688
689 a = Big.DP;
690 b = Big.RM;
691 Big.DP = Big.RM = 0;
692 x = x.div(y);
693 Big.DP = a;
694 Big.RM = b;
695
696 return this.minus(x.times(y));
697 };
698
699
700 /*
701 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big plus the value of Big y.
702 */
703 P.plus = P.add = function (y) {
704 var t,
705 x = this,
706 Big = x.constructor,
707 a = x.s,
708 b = (y = new Big(y)).s;
709
710 // Signs differ?
711 if (a != b) {
712 y.s = -b;
713 return x.minus(y);
714 }
715
716 var xe = x.e,
717 xc = x.c,
718 ye = y.e,
719 yc = y.c;
720
721 // Either zero? y is non-zero? x is non-zero? Or both are zero.
722 if (!xc[0] || !yc[0]) return yc[0] ? y : new Big(xc[0] ? x : a * 0);
723
724 xc = xc.slice();
725
726 // Prepend zeros to equalise exponents.
727 // Note: Faster to use reverse than do unshifts.
728 if (a = xe - ye) {
729 if (a > 0) {
730 ye = xe;
731 t = yc;
732 } else {
733 a = -a;
734 t = xc;
735 }
736
737 t.reverse();
738 for (; a--;) t.push(0);
739 t.reverse();
740 }
741
742 // Point xc to the longer array.
743 if (xc.length - yc.length < 0) {
744 t = yc;
745 yc = xc;
746 xc = t;
747 }
748
749 a = yc.length;
750
751 // Only start adding at yc.length - 1 as the further digits of xc can be left as they are.
752 for (b = 0; a; xc[a] %= 10) b = (xc[--a] = xc[a] + yc[a] + b) / 10 | 0;
753
754 // No need to check for zero, as +x + +y != 0 && -x + -y != 0
755
756 if (b) {
757 xc.unshift(b);
758 ++ye;
759 }
760
761 // Remove trailing zeros.
762 for (a = xc.length; xc[--a] === 0;) xc.pop();
763
764 y.c = xc;
765 y.e = ye;
766
767 return y;
768 };
769
770
771 /*
772 * Return a Big whose value is the value of this Big raised to the power n.
773 * If n is negative, round to a maximum of Big.DP decimal places using rounding
774 * mode Big.RM.
775 *
776 * n {number} Integer, -MAX_POWER to MAX_POWER inclusive.
777 */
778 P.pow = function (n) {
779 var x = this,
780 one = new x.constructor(1),
781 y = one,
782 isneg = n < 0;
783
784 if (n !== ~~n || n < -MAX_POWER || n > MAX_POWER) throw Error(INVALID + 'exponent');
785 if (isneg) n = -n;
786
787 for (;;) {
788 if (n & 1) y = y.times(x);
789 n >>= 1;
790 if (!n) break;
791 x = x.times(x);
792 }
793
794 return isneg ? one.div(y) : y;
795 };
796
797
798 /*
799 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big rounded to a maximum of dp decimal
800 * places using rounding mode rm.
801 * If dp is not specified, round to 0 decimal places.
802 * If rm is not specified, use Big.RM.
803 *
804 * dp? {number} Integer, 0 to MAX_DP inclusive.
805 * rm? 0, 1, 2 or 3 (ROUND_DOWN, ROUND_HALF_UP, ROUND_HALF_EVEN, ROUND_UP)
806 */
807 P.round = function (dp, rm) {
808 var Big = this.constructor;
809 if (dp === UNDEFINED) dp = 0;
810 else if (dp !== ~~dp || dp < 0 || dp > MAX_DP) throw Error(INVALID_DP);
811 return round(new Big(this), dp, rm === UNDEFINED ? Big.RM : rm);
812 };
813
814
815 /*
816 * Return a new Big whose value is the square root of the value of this Big, rounded, if
817 * necessary, to a maximum of Big.DP decimal places using rounding mode Big.RM.
818 */
819 P.sqrt = function () {
820 var r, c, t,
821 x = this,
822 Big = x.constructor,
823 s = x.s,
824 e = x.e,
825 half = new Big(0.5);
826
827 // Zero?
828 if (!x.c[0]) return new Big(x);
829
830 // Negative?
831 if (s < 0) throw Error(NAME + 'No square root');
832
833 // Estimate.
834 s = Math.sqrt(x.toString());
835
836 // Math.sqrt underflow/overflow?
837 // Re-estimate: pass x to Math.sqrt as integer, then adjust the result exponent.
838 if (s === 0 || s === 1 / 0) {
839 c = x.c.join('');
840 if (!(c.length + e & 1)) c += '0';
841 r = new Big(Math.sqrt(c).toString());
842 r.e = ((e + 1) / 2 | 0) - (e < 0 || e & 1);
843 } else {
844 r = new Big(s.toString());
845 }
846
847 e = r.e + (Big.DP += 4);
848
849 // Newton-Raphson iteration.
850 do {
851 t = r;
852 r = half.times(t.plus(x.div(t)));
853 } while (t.c.slice(0, e).join('') !== r.c.slice(0, e).join(''));
854
855 return round(r, Big.DP -= 4, Big.RM);
856 };
857
858
859 /*
860 * Return a new Big whose value is the value of this Big times the value of Big y.
861 */
862 P.times = P.mul = function (y) {
863 var c,
864 x = this,
865 Big = x.constructor,
866 xc = x.c,
867 yc = (y = new Big(y)).c,
868 a = xc.length,
869 b = yc.length,
870 i = x.e,
871 j = y.e;
872
873 // Determine sign of result.
874 y.s = x.s == y.s ? 1 : -1;
875
876 // Return signed 0 if either 0.
877 if (!xc[0] || !yc[0]) return new Big(y.s * 0);
878
879 // Initialise exponent of result as x.e + y.e.
880 y.e = i + j;
881
882 // If array xc has fewer digits than yc, swap xc and yc, and lengths.
883 if (a < b) {
884 c = xc;
885 xc = yc;
886 yc = c;
887 j = a;
888 a = b;
889 b = j;
890 }
891
892 // Initialise coefficient array of result with zeros.
893 for (c = new Array(j = a + b); j--;) c[j] = 0;
894
895 // Multiply.
896
897 // i is initially xc.length.
898 for (i = b; i--;) {
899 b = 0;
900
901 // a is yc.length.
902 for (j = a + i; j > i;) {
903
904 // Current sum of products at this digit position, plus carry.
905 b = c[j] + yc[i] * xc[j - i - 1] + b;
906 c[j--] = b % 10;
907
908 // carry
909 b = b / 10 | 0;
910 }
911
912 c[j] = (c[j] + b) % 10;
913 }
914
915 // Increment result exponent if there is a final carry, otherwise remove leading zero.
916 if (b) ++y.e;
917 else c.shift();
918
919 // Remove trailing zeros.
920 for (i = c.length; !c[--i];) c.pop();
921 y.c = c;
922
923 return y;
924 };
925
926
927 /*
928 * Return a string representing the value of this Big in exponential notation to dp fixed decimal
929 * places and rounded using Big.RM.
930 *
931 * dp? {number} Integer, 0 to MAX_DP inclusive.
932 */
933 P.toExponential = function (dp) {
934 return stringify(this, 1, dp, dp);
935 };
936
937
938 /*
939 * Return a string representing the value of this Big in normal notation to dp fixed decimal
940 * places and rounded using Big.RM.
941 *
942 * dp? {number} Integer, 0 to MAX_DP inclusive.
943 *
944 * (-0).toFixed(0) is '0', but (-0.1).toFixed(0) is '-0'.
945 * (-0).toFixed(1) is '0.0', but (-0.01).toFixed(1) is '-0.0'.
946 */
947 P.toFixed = function (dp) {
948 return stringify(this, 2, dp, this.e + dp);
949 };
950
951
952 /*
953 * Return a string representing the value of this Big rounded to sd significant digits using
954 * Big.RM. Use exponential notation if sd is less than the number of digits necessary to represent
955 * the integer part of the value in normal notation.
956 *
957 * sd {number} Integer, 1 to MAX_DP inclusive.
958 */
959 P.toPrecision = function (sd) {
960 return stringify(this, 3, sd, sd - 1);
961 };
962
963
964 /*
965 * Return a string representing the value of this Big.
966 * Return exponential notation if this Big has a positive exponent equal to or greater than
967 * Big.PE, or a negative exponent equal to or less than Big.NE.
968 * Omit the sign for negative zero.
969 */
970 P.toString = function () {
971 return stringify(this);
972 };
973
974
975 /*
976 * Return a string representing the value of this Big.
977 * Return exponential notation if this Big has a positive exponent equal to or greater than
978 * Big.PE, or a negative exponent equal to or less than Big.NE.
979 * Include the sign for negative zero.
980 */
981 P.valueOf = P.toJSON = function () {
982 return stringify(this, 4);
983 };
984
985
986 // Export
987
988
989 Big = _Big_();
990
991 Big['default'] = Big.Big = Big;
992
993 //AMD.
994 if (typeof define === 'function' && define.amd) {
995 define(function () { return Big; });
996
997 // Node and other CommonJS-like environments that support module.exports.
998 } else if (typeof module !== 'undefined' && module.exports) {
999 module.exports = Big;
1000
1001 //Browser.
1002 } else {
1003 GLOBAL.Big = Big;
1004 }
1005})(this);
1006)CODE";
1007
1008 // Prepare code template
1009 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
1010
1011 Write(code);
1012
1013 // Generate common footer
1014 GenerateFooter();
1015
1016 // Close the common file
1017 WriteEnd();
1018 Store(common);
1019}

1184 static fromString (str, radix = 10) {
1185 if (str.length === 0) {
1186 throw new Error('Empty string!')
1187 }
1188 if ((str === 'NaN') || (str === 'Infinity') || (str === '+Infinity') || (str === '-Infinity')) {
1189 return INT64_ZERO
1190 }

1192 if ((radix < 2) || (radix > 36)) {

1214 } else {
1215 result = result.mul(radixToPower)
1216 result = result.add(Int64.fromNumber(value))
1217 }

1649 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1650 other = Int64.fromValue(other)

1655 }

1658 }

1661 }

1676 }

1679 // We can skip products that would overflow.

1682 let a32 = this.high & 0xFFFF
1683 let a16 = this.low >>> 16
1684 let a00 = this.low & 0xFFFF
1685

1687 let b32 = other.high & 0xFFFF
1688 let b16 = other.low >>> 16

1716 }
1717
1724 div (other) {
1725 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1726 other = Int64.fromValue(other)
1727 }
1728 if (other.isZero) {
1729 throw new Error('Division by zero!')
1730 }
1731
1732 if (this.isZero) {
1733 return INT64_ZERO
1734 }
1735
1736 let approx, rem, res
1737
1738 // This section is only relevant for signed longs and is derived from the closure library as a whole
1739 if (this.eq(INT64_MIN)) {
1740 // Recall that -MIN_VALUE == MIN_VALUE
1741 if (other.eq(INT64_ONE) || other.eq(INT64_NEG_ONE)) {
1742 return INT64_MIN
1743 } else if (other.eq(INT64_MIN)) {
1744 return INT64_ONE
1745 } else {
1746 // At this point, we have |other| >= 2, so |this/other| < |MIN_VALUE|
1747 let halfThis = this.shr(1)
1748 approx = halfThis.div(other).shl(1)
1749 if (approx.eq(INT64_ZERO)) {
1750 return other.isNegative ? INT64_ONE : INT64_NEG_ONE
1751 } else {
1752 rem = this.sub(other.mul(approx))
1753 res = approx.add(rem.div(other))
1754 return res
1755 }
1756 }
1757 } else if (other.eq(INT64_MIN)) {
1758 return INT64_ZERO
1759 }
1760
1761 if (this.isNegative) {
1762 if (other.isNegative) {
1763 return this.neg().div(other.neg())
1764 }
1765 return this.neg().div(other).neg()
1766 } else if (other.isNegative) {
1767 return this.div(other.neg()).neg()
1768 }
1769 res = INT64_ZERO
1770
1771 // Repeat the following until the remainder is less than other: find a floating-point that approximates
1772 // remainder / other *from below*, add this into the result, and subtract it from the remainder.
1773 // It is critical that the approximate value is less than or equal to the real value so that the
1774 // remainder never becomes negative.
1775 rem = this
1776 while (rem.gte(other)) {
1777 // Approximate the result of division. This may be a little greater or smaller than the actual value
1778 approx = Math.max(1, Math.floor(rem.toNumber() / other.toNumber()))
1779
1780 // We will tweak the approximate result by changing it in the 48-th digit or the smallest non-fractional
1781 // digit, whichever is larger.
1782 let log2 = Math.ceil(Math.log(approx) / Math.LN2)
1783 let delta = (log2 <= 48) ? 1 : Math.pow(2, log2 - 48)
1784
1785 // Decrease the approximation until it is smaller than the remainder.
1786 // Note that if it is too large, the product overflows and is negative.
1787 let approxRes = Int64.fromNumber(approx)
1788 let approxRem = approxRes.mul(other)
1789 while (approxRem.isNegative || approxRem.gt(rem)) {
1790 approx -= delta
1791 approxRes = Int64.fromNumber(approx)
1792 approxRem = approxRes.mul(other)
1793 }
1794

1796 // we would make no progress.
1797 if (approxRes.isZero) {
1798 approxRes = INT64_ONE
1799 }
1800
1801 res = res.add(approxRes)
1802 rem = rem.sub(approxRem)
1803 }
1804 return res
1805 }
1806
1813 mod (other) {
1814 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1815 other = Int64.fromValue(other)
1816 }

1818 }
1819
1825 not () {

1827 }
1828
1835 and (other) {
1836 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1837 other = Int64.fromValue(other)
1838 }
1839 return Int64.fromBits(this.low & other.low, this.high & other.high)
1840 }
1841
1848 or (other) {
1849 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1850 other = Int64.fromValue(other)
1851 }
1852 return Int64.fromBits(this.low | other.low, this.high | other.high)
1853 }
1854
1861 xor (other) {
1862 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
1863 other = Int64.fromValue(other)
1864 }
1865 return Int64.fromBits(this.low ^ other.low, this.high ^ other.high)
1866 }
1867
1874 shl (numBits) {
1875 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
1876 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
1877 }
1878 if ((numBits &= 63) === 0) {
1879 return this
1880 } else if (numBits < 32) {
1881 return Int64.fromBits(this.low << numBits, (this.high << numBits) | (this.low >>> (32 - numBits)))
1882 } else {
1883 return Int64.fromBits(0, this.low << (numBits - 32))
1884 }
1885 }
1886

1894 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
1895 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
1896 }
1897 if ((numBits &= 63) === 0) {
1898 return this
1899 } else if (numBits < 32) {
1900 return Int64.fromBits((this.low >>> numBits) | (this.high << (32 - numBits)), this.high >> numBits)
1901 } else {
1902 return Int64.fromBits(this.high >> (numBits - 32), (this.high >= 0) ? 0 : -1)
1903 }
1904 }

1913 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
1914 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
1915 }
1916 numBits &= 63
1917 if (numBits === 0) {
1918 return this
1919 } else {
1920 let high = this.high
1921 if (numBits < 32) {
1922 let low = this.low
1923 return Int64.fromBits((low >>> numBits) | (high << (32 - numBits)), high >>> numBits)
1924 } else if (numBits === 32) {
1925 return Int64.fromBits(high, 0)
1926 } else {
1927 return Int64.fromBits(high >>> (numBits - 32), 0)
1928 }
1929 }
1930 }

2112 static fromString (str, radix = 10) {
2113 if (str.length === 0) {
2114 throw new Error('Empty string!')
2115 }
2116 if ((str === 'NaN') || (str === 'Infinity') || (str === '+Infinity') || (str === '-Infinity')) {
2117 return UINT64_ZERO
2118 }

2121 throw new RangeError('radix')
2122 }

2132 // minimize the calls to the very expensive emulated div.

2142 } else {
2143 result = result.mul(radixToPower)
2144 result = result.add(UInt64.fromNumber(value))

2500 code = R"CODE(
2506 neg () {
2507 return this.not().add(UINT64_ONE)

2516 add (other) {
2517 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2518 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2519 }
2520
2521 // Divide each number into 4 chunks of 16 bits, and then sum the chunks
2522
2523 let a48 = this.high >>> 16
2524 let a32 = this.high & 0xFFFF
2525 let a16 = this.low >>> 16
2526 let a00 = this.low & 0xFFFF
2527
2528 let b48 = other.high >>> 16
2529 let b32 = other.high & 0xFFFF
2530 let b16 = other.low >>> 16
2531 let b00 = other.low & 0xFFFF
2532
2533 let c48 = 0
2534 let c32 = 0
2535 let c16 = 0
2536 let c00 = 0
2537 c00 += a00 + b00
2538 c16 += c00 >>> 16
2539 c00 &= 0xFFFF
2540 c16 += a16 + b16
2541 c32 += c16 >>> 16
2542 c16 &= 0xFFFF
2543 c32 += a32 + b32
2544 c48 += c32 >>> 16
2545 c32 &= 0xFFFF

2547 c48 &= 0xFFFF

2557 sub (other) {
2558 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2559 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2560 }
2561 return this.add(other.neg())
2562 }
2563
2570 mul (other) {
2571 if (this.isZero) {
2572 return UINT64_ZERO
2573 }
2574 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2575 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2576 }
2577
2578 if (other.isZero) {
2579 return UINT64_ZERO
2580 }
2581 if (this.eq(UINT64_MIN)) {
2582 return other.isOdd ? UINT64_MIN : UINT64_ZERO
2583 }
2584 if (other.eq(UINT64_MIN)) {
2585 return this.isOdd ? UINT64_MIN : UINT64_ZERO
2586 }
2587
2588 if (this.isNegative) {
2589 if (other.isNegative) {
2590 return this.neg().mul(other.neg())
2591 } else {
2592 return this.neg().mul(other).neg()
2593 }
2594 } else if (other.isNegative) {
2595 return this.mul(other.neg()).neg()
2596 }
2597
2598 // If both longs are small, use float multiplication
2599 if (this.lt(UINT64_TWO_PWR_24) && other.lt(UINT64_TWO_PWR_24)) {
2600 return UInt64.fromNumber(this.toNumber() * other.toNumber())
2601 }
2602
2603 // Divide each long into 4 chunks of 16 bits, and then add up 4x4 products.
2604 // We can skip products that would overflow.
2605
2606 let a48 = this.high >>> 16
2607 let a32 = this.high & 0xFFFF
2608 let a16 = this.low >>> 16
2609 let a00 = this.low & 0xFFFF
2610
2611 let b48 = other.high >>> 16
2612 let b32 = other.high & 0xFFFF
2613 let b16 = other.low >>> 16
2614 let b00 = other.low & 0xFFFF
2615
2616 let c48 = 0
2617 let c32 = 0
2618 let c16 = 0
2619 let c00 = 0
2620 c00 += a00 * b00
2621 c16 += c00 >>> 16
2622 c00 &= 0xFFFF
2623 c16 += a16 * b00
2624 c32 += c16 >>> 16
2625 c16 &= 0xFFFF
2626 c16 += a00 * b16
2627 c32 += c16 >>> 16
2628 c16 &= 0xFFFF
2629 c32 += a32 * b00

2631 c32 &= 0xFFFF
2632 c32 += a16 * b16
2633 c48 += c32 >>> 16

2635 c32 += a00 * b32

2639 c48 &= 0xFFFF
2640 return UInt64.fromBits((c16 << 16) | c00, (c48 << 16) | c32)
2641 }
2642
2649 div (other) {
2650 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2651 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2652 }
2653 if (other.isZero) {
2654 throw new Error('Division by zero!')
2655 }
2656
2657 if (this.isZero) {
2658 return UINT64_ZERO
2659 }
2660
2661 let approx, rem, res
2662
2663 // The algorithm below has not been made for unsigned longs. It's therefore required to take special care of
2664 // the MSB prior to running it.
2665 if (Int64.isInt64(other)) {
2666 other = other.toUnsigned()
2667 }
2668 if (other.gt(this)) {
2669 return UINT64_ZERO
2670 }
2671 // 15 >>> 1 = 7 ; with divisor = 8 ; true
2672 if (other.gt(this.shru(1))) {
2673 return UINT64_ONE
2674 }
2675 res = UINT64_ZERO
2676
2677 // Repeat the following until the remainder is less than other: find a floating-point that approximates
2678 // remainder / other *from below*, add this into the result, and subtract it from the remainder.
2679 // It is critical that the approximate value is less than or equal to the real value so that the
2680 // remainder never becomes negative.
2681 rem = this
2682 while (rem.gte(other)) {
2683 // Approximate the result of division. This may be a little greater or smaller than the actual value
2684 approx = Math.max(1, Math.floor(rem.toNumber() / other.toNumber()))
2685
2686 // We will tweak the approximate result by changing it in the 48-th digit or the smallest non-fractional
2687 // digit, whichever is larger.
2688 let log2 = Math.ceil(Math.log(approx) / Math.LN2)
2689 let delta = (log2 <= 48) ? 1 : Math.pow(2, log2 - 48)
2690
2691 // Decrease the approximation until it is smaller than the remainder.
2692 // Note that if it is too large, the product overflows and is negative.
2693 let approxRes = Int64.fromNumber(approx)
2694 let approxRem = approxRes.mul(other)
2695 while (approxRem.isNegative || approxRem.gt(rem)) {
2696 approx -= delta
2697 approxRes = UInt64.fromNumber(approx)
2698 approxRem = approxRes.mul(other)
2699 }
2700
2701 // We know the answer can't be zero... and actually, zero would cause infinite recursion since
2702 // we would make no progress.
2703 if (approxRes.isZero) {
2704 approxRes = UINT64_ONE
2705 }
2706
2707 res = res.add(approxRes)
2708 rem = rem.sub(approxRem)
2709 }
2710 return res
2711 }
2712
2719 mod (other) {
2720 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2721 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2722 }
2723 return this.sub(this.div(other).mul(other))
2724 }
2725
2731 not () {
2732 return UInt64.fromBits(~this.low, ~this.high)
2733 }
2734
2741 and (other) {
2742 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2743 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2744 }
2745 return UInt64.fromBits(this.low & other.low, this.high & other.high)
2746 }
2747
2754 or (other) {
2755 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2756 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2757 }
2758 return UInt64.fromBits(this.low | other.low, this.high | other.high)
2759 }
2760
2767 xor (other) {
2768 if (!Int64.isInt64(other) && !UInt64.isUInt64(other)) {
2769 other = UInt64.fromValue(other)
2770 }
2771 return UInt64.fromBits(this.low ^ other.low, this.high ^ other.high)
2772 }
2773
2780 shl (numBits) {
2781 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
2782 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
2783 }
2784 if ((numBits &= 63) === 0) {
2785 return this
2786 } else if (numBits < 32) {
2787 return UInt64.fromBits(this.low << numBits, (this.high << numBits) | (this.low >>> (32 - numBits)))
2788 } else {
2789 return UInt64.fromBits(0, this.low << (numBits - 32))
2790 }
2791 }
2792
2799 shr (numBits) {
2800 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
2801 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
2802 }
2803 if ((numBits &= 63) === 0) {
2804 return this
2805 } else if (numBits < 32) {
2806 return UInt64.fromBits((this.low >>> numBits) | (this.high << (32 - numBits)), this.high >> numBits)
2807 } else {
2808 return UInt64.fromBits(this.high >> (numBits - 32), (this.high >= 0) ? 0 : -1)
2809 }
2810 }
2811
2818 shru (numBits) {
2819 if (Int64.isInt64(numBits) || UInt64.isUInt64(numBits)) {
2820 numBits = numBits.toInt32()
2821 }
2822 numBits &= 63
2823 if (numBits === 0) {
2824 return this
2825 } else {
2826 let high = this.high
2827 if (numBits < 32) {
2828 let low = this.low
2829 return UInt64.fromBits((low >>> numBits) | (high << (32 - numBits)), high >>> numBits)
2830 } else if (numBits === 32) {
2831 return UInt64.fromBits(high, 0)
2832 } else {
2833 return UInt64.fromBits(high >>> (numBits - 32), 0)
2834 }
2835 }

2845const UINT64_TWO_PWR_64_DBL = UINT64_TWO_PWR_32_DBL * UINT64_TWO_PWR_32_DBL

2852const UINT64_ONE = UInt64.fromInt32(1)
2853const UINT64_MIN = UInt64.fromInt32(0)
2854const UINT64_MAX = UInt64.fromBits(0xFFFFFFFF | 0, 0xFFFFFFFF | 0)
2855const UINT64_TWO_PWR_24 = UInt64.fromInt32(UINT64_TWO_PWR_24_DBL)
2856
2857exports.UInt64 = UInt64
2858)CODE";
2859

2861 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
2862

2864

2866 GenerateFooter();

2869 WriteEnd();

2883/* eslint-disable prefer-const,no-loss-of-precision */

2885
2900class UUID {
2906 constructor (value = undefined) {
2907 if (value == null) {
2908 this.data = new Uint8Array(16)
2909 } else if ((value instanceof Array) || (value instanceof Uint8Array)) {
2910 this.data = UUID.fromBytes(value).data.slice()
2911 } else if ((typeof value === 'string') || (value instanceof String)) {
2912 this.data = UUID.fromString(value).data.slice()
2913 } else if (value instanceof UUID) {
2914 this.data = value.data.slice()
2915 } else {

2919
2925 static isUUID (obj) {
2926 return (obj && obj.__isUUID__) === true
2927 }

2934 static fromBytes (bytes) {

2954 static fromParts (timeLow, timeMid, timeHiAndVersion, clockSeqHiAndReserved, clockSeqLow, nodeLow, nodeMid, nodeHi) {

3004 static sequential () {
3005 let now = new Date().getTime()
3006 let sequence = Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_14)
3007 let nodeHi = Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_8)
3008 let nodeMid = Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_8)

3020 } else if ((Math.random() < timestampRatio) && (tick < 9984)) {

3045 Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_16),

3047 0x80 | Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_6),
3048 Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_8),
3049 Math.floor(Math.random() * TWO_POW_32),

3060 toBytes () {

3084
3091 eq (other) {

3102

3111 }

3119 lt (other) {
3120 return this.cmp(other) < 0
3121 }
3122
3129 lte (other) {
3130 return this.cmp(other) <= 0
3131 }
3132
3139 gt (other) {

3141 }

3149 gte (other) {

3161 return 1
3162 }

3164 let diff = this.data[i] - other.data[i]
3165 if (diff !== 0) {

3200void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateIEEE754(const CppCommon::Path& path)
3201{
3202 // Generate the common file
3203 CppCommon::Path common = path / "ieee754.js";
3204 WriteBegin();
3205
3206 // Generate common header
3207 GenerateHeader("FBE");
3208
3209 std::string code = R"CODE(
3210/* eslint-disable prefer-const,no-loss-of-precision */
3211'use strict'
3212
3222let ieee754read = function (buffer, offset, isLE, mLen, nBytes) {
3223 let e, m
3224 let eLen = (nBytes * 8) - mLen - 1
3225 let eMax = (1 << eLen) - 1
3226 let eBias = eMax >> 1
3227 let nBits = -7
3228 let i = isLE ? (nBytes - 1) : 0
3229 let d = isLE ? -1 : 1
3230 let s = buffer[offset + i]
3231
3232 i += d
3233
3234 e = s & ((1 << (-nBits)) - 1)
3235 s >>= (-nBits)
3236 nBits += eLen
3237 for (; nBits > 0; e = (e * 256) + buffer[offset + i], i += d, nBits -= 8);
3238
3239 m = e & ((1 << (-nBits)) - 1)
3240 e >>= (-nBits)
3241 nBits += mLen
3242 for (; nBits > 0; m = (m * 256) + buffer[offset + i], i += d, nBits -= 8);
3243
3244 if (e === 0) {
3245 e = 1 - eBias
3246 } else if (e === eMax) {
3247 return m ? NaN : ((s ? -1 : 1) * Infinity)
3248 } else {
3249 m = m + Math.pow(2, mLen)
3250 e = e - eBias
3251 }
3252 return (s ? -1 : 1) * m * Math.pow(2, e - mLen)
3253}
3254
3255exports.ieee754read = ieee754read
3256
3266let ieee754write = function (buffer, offset, value, isLE, mLen, nBytes) {
3267 let e, m, c
3268 let eLen = (nBytes * 8) - mLen - 1
3269 let eMax = (1 << eLen) - 1
3270 let eBias = eMax >> 1
3271 let rt = (mLen === 23 ? Math.pow(2, -24) - Math.pow(2, -77) : 0)
3272 let i = isLE ? 0 : (nBytes - 1)
3273 let d = isLE ? 1 : -1
3274 let s = value < 0 || (value === 0 && 1 / value < 0) ? 1 : 0
3275
3276 value = Math.abs(value)
3277
3278 if (isNaN(value) || value === Infinity) {
3279 m = isNaN(value) ? 1 : 0
3280 e = eMax
3281 } else {
3282 e = Math.floor(Math.log(value) / Math.LN2)
3283 if (value * (c = Math.pow(2, -e)) < 1) {
3284 e--
3285 c *= 2
3286 }
3287 if (e + eBias >= 1) {
3288 value += rt / c
3289 } else {
3290 value += rt * Math.pow(2, 1 - eBias)
3291 }
3292 if (value * c >= 2) {
3293 e++
3294 c /= 2
3295 }
3296
3297 if (e + eBias >= eMax) {
3298 m = 0
3299 e = eMax
3300 } else if (e + eBias >= 1) {
3301 m = ((value * c) - 1) * Math.pow(2, mLen)
3302 e = e + eBias
3303 } else {
3304 m = value * Math.pow(2, eBias - 1) * Math.pow(2, mLen)
3305 e = 0
3306 }
3307 }
3308
3309 for (; mLen >= 8; buffer[offset + i] = m & 0xff, i += d, m /= 256, mLen -= 8);
3310
3311 e = (e << mLen) | m
3312 eLen += mLen
3313 for (; eLen > 0; buffer[offset + i] = e & 0xff, i += d, e /= 256, eLen -= 8);
3314
3315 buffer[offset + i - d] |= s * 128
3316}
3317
3318exports.ieee754write = ieee754write
3319)CODE";
3320
3321 // Prepare code template
3322 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
3323
3324 Write(code);
3325
3326 // Generate common footer
3327 GenerateFooter();
3328
3329 // Close the common file
3330 WriteEnd();
3331 Store(common);
3332}
3333
3334void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateUTF8(const CppCommon::Path& path)
3335{
3336 // Generate the common file
3337 CppCommon::Path common = path / "utf8.js";
3338 WriteBegin();
3339
3340 // Generate common header
3341 GenerateHeader("FBE");
3342
3343 std::string code = R"CODE(
3344/* eslint-disable prefer-const,no-loss-of-precision */
3345'use strict'
3346
3352let utf8count = function (str) {
3353 let bytes = 0
3354 for (let i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
3355 let codePoint = str.charCodeAt(i)
3356 if (codePoint < 0x80) {
3357 bytes++
3358 } else if ((codePoint > 0x7F) && (codePoint < 0x800)) {
3359 bytes = bytes + 2
3360 } else {
3361 bytes = bytes + 3
3362 }
3363 }
3364 return bytes
3365}
3366
3367exports.utf8count = utf8count
3368
3375let utf8encode = function (buffer, offset, str) {
3376 let units = Infinity
3377 let codePoint
3378 let index = offset
3379 let length = str.length
3380 let leadSurrogate = null
3381
3382 for (let i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
3383 codePoint = str.charCodeAt(i)
3384
3385 // Is surrogate component...
3386 if ((codePoint > 0xD7FF) && (codePoint < 0xE000)) {
3387 // Last char was a lead
3388 if (!leadSurrogate) {
3389 // No lead yet
3390 if (codePoint > 0xDBFF) {
3391 // Unexpected trail
3392 if ((units -= 3) > -1) {
3393 buffer[index++] = 0xEF
3394 buffer[index++] = 0xBF
3395 buffer[index++] = 0xBD
3396 }
3397 continue
3398 } else if ((i + 1) === length) {
3399 // Unpaired lead
3400 if ((units -= 3) > -1) {
3401 buffer[index++] = 0xEF
3402 buffer[index++] = 0xBF
3403 buffer[index++] = 0xBD
3404 }
3405 continue
3406 }
3407
3408 // Valid lead
3409 leadSurrogate = codePoint
3410
3411 continue
3412 }
3413
3414 // 2 leads in a row
3415 if (codePoint < 0xDC00) {
3416 if ((units -= 3) > -1) {
3417 buffer[index++] = 0xEF
3418 buffer[index++] = 0xBF
3419 buffer[index++] = 0xBD
3420 }
3421 leadSurrogate = codePoint
3422 continue
3423 }
3424
3425 // Valid surrogate pair
3426 codePoint = (((leadSurrogate - 0xD800) << 10) | (codePoint - 0xDC00)) + 0x10000
3427 } else if (leadSurrogate) {
3428 // Valid bmp char, but last char was a lead
3429 if ((units -= 3) > -1) {
3430 buffer[index++] = 0xEF
3431 buffer[index++] = 0xBF
3432 buffer[index++] = 0xBD
3433 }
3434 }
3435
3436 leadSurrogate = null
3437
3438 // Encode utf8
3439 if (codePoint < 0x80) {
3440 if ((units -= 1) < 0) {
3441 break
3442 }
3443 buffer[index++] = codePoint
3444 } else if (codePoint < 0x800) {
3445 if ((units -= 2) < 0) {
3446 break
3447 }
3448 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0x6 | 0xC0
3449 buffer[index++] = codePoint & 0x3F | 0x80
3450 } else if (codePoint < 0x10000) {
3451 if ((units -= 3) < 0) {
3452 break
3453 }
3454 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0xC | 0xE0
3455 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0x6 & 0x3F | 0x80
3456 buffer[index++] = codePoint & 0x3F | 0x80
3457 } else if (codePoint < 0x110000) {
3458 if ((units -= 4) < 0) {
3459 break
3460 }
3461 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0x12 | 0xF0
3462 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0xC & 0x3F | 0x80
3463 buffer[index++] = codePoint >> 0x6 & 0x3F | 0x80
3464 buffer[index++] = codePoint & 0x3F | 0x80
3465 } else {
3466 throw new Error('Invalid code point!')
3467 }
3468 }
3469}
3470
3471exports.utf8encode = utf8encode
3472
3480let utf8decode = function (buffer, offset, size) {
3481 let start = offset
3482 let end = offset + size
3483 let res = []
3484
3485 let i = start
3486 while (i < end) {
3487 let firstByte = buffer[i]
3488 let codePoint = null
3489 let bytesPerSequence = (firstByte > 0xEF) ? 4 : ((firstByte > 0xDF) ? 3 : ((firstByte > 0xBF) ? 2 : 1))
3490
3491 if ((i + bytesPerSequence) <= end) {
3492 let secondByte
3493 let thirdByte
3494 let fourthByte
3495 let tempCodePoint
3496
3497 switch (bytesPerSequence) {
3498 case 1:
3499 if (firstByte < 0x80) {
3500 codePoint = firstByte
3501 }
3502 break
3503 case 2:
3504 secondByte = buffer[i + 1]
3505 if ((secondByte & 0xC0) === 0x80) {
3506 tempCodePoint = ((firstByte & 0x1F) << 0x6) | (secondByte & 0x3F)
3507 if (tempCodePoint > 0x7F) {
3508 codePoint = tempCodePoint
3509 }
3510 }
3511 break
3512 case 3:
3513 secondByte = buffer[i + 1]
3514 thirdByte = buffer[i + 2]
3515 if (((secondByte & 0xC0) === 0x80) && ((thirdByte & 0xC0) === 0x80)) {
3516 tempCodePoint = ((firstByte & 0xF) << 0xC) | ((secondByte & 0x3F) << 0x6) | (thirdByte & 0x3F)
3517 if ((tempCodePoint > 0x7FF) && ((tempCodePoint < 0xD800) || (tempCodePoint > 0xDFFF))) {
3518 codePoint = tempCodePoint
3519 }
3520 }
3521 break
3522 case 4:
3523 secondByte = buffer[i + 1]
3524 thirdByte = buffer[i + 2]
3525 fourthByte = buffer[i + 3]
3526 if (((secondByte & 0xC0) === 0x80) && ((thirdByte & 0xC0) === 0x80) && ((fourthByte & 0xC0) === 0x80)) {
3527 tempCodePoint = ((firstByte & 0xF) << 0x12) | ((secondByte & 0x3F) << 0xC) | ((thirdByte & 0x3F) << 0x6) | (fourthByte & 0x3F)
3528 if ((tempCodePoint > 0xFFFF) && (tempCodePoint < 0x110000)) {
3529 codePoint = tempCodePoint
3530 }
3531 }
3532 }
3533 }
3534
3535 if (codePoint === null) {
3536 // We did not generate a valid codePoint so insert a replacement char (U+FFFD) and advance only 1 byte
3537 codePoint = 0xFFFD
3538 bytesPerSequence = 1
3539 } else if (codePoint > 0xFFFF) {
3540 // Encode to utf16 (surrogate pair dance)
3541 codePoint -= 0x10000
3542 res.push((codePoint >>> 10) & 0x3FF | 0xD800)
3543 codePoint = 0xDC00 | codePoint & 0x3FF
3544 }
3545
3546 res.push(codePoint)
3547 i += bytesPerSequence
3548 }
3549
3550 // Based on http://stackoverflow.com/a/22747272/680742, the browser with the lowest limit is Chrome, with 0x10000 args.
3551 // We go 1 magnitude less, for safety
3552 const MAX_ARGUMENTS_LENGTH = 0x1000
3553
3554 if (res.length <= MAX_ARGUMENTS_LENGTH) {
3555 // Avoid extra slice()
3556 return String.fromCharCode.apply(String, res)
3557 }
3558
3559 let result = ''
3560
3561 // Decode in chunks to avoid "call stack size exceeded"
3562 i = 0
3563 while (i < res.length) {
3564 result += String.fromCharCode.apply(String, res.slice(i, i += MAX_ARGUMENTS_LENGTH))
3565 }
3566
3567 return result
3568}
3569
3570exports.utf8decode = utf8decode
3571)CODE";
3572
3573 // Prepare code template
3574 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
3575
3576 Write(code);
3577
3578 // Generate common footer
3579 GenerateFooter();
3580
3581 // Close the common file
3582 WriteEnd();
3583 Store(common);
3584}

3675 GenerateFBEFinalModelOptional();
3676 GenerateFBEFinalModelArray();
3677 GenerateFBEFinalModelVector();
3678 GenerateFBEFinalModelSet();
3679 GenerateFBEFinalModelMap();
3680 }
3681 if (Proto())
3682 {
3683 GenerateFBESender();
3684 GenerateFBEReceiver();
3685 GenerateFBEClient();
3686 }
3687 if (JSON())
3688 GenerateFBEJson();
3689
3690 // Generate common footer
3691 GenerateFooter();
3692
3693 // Close the common file
3694 WriteEnd();
3695 Store(common);
3696}

3861void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEWriteBuffer()
3862{
3863 std::string code = R"CODE(
3867class WriteBuffer extends BaseBuffer {
3873 constructor (capacity = 0) {
3874 super()
3875 this._buffer = new Uint8Array(capacity)
3876 this._size = 0
3877 this._offset = 0
3878 }
3879
3884 attachNew () {
3885 this._buffer = new Uint8Array(0)
3886 this._size = 0
3887 this._offset = 0
3888 }
3889
3895 attachCapacity (capacity = 0) {
3896 this._buffer = new Uint8Array(capacity)
3897 this._size = 0
3898 this._offset = 0
3899 }
3900
3908 attachBuffer (buffer, offset = 0, size = undefined) {
3909 if (size == null) {
3910 size = buffer.length
3911 }
3912
3913 if (size <= 0) {
3914 throw new Error('Invalid size!')
3915 }
3916 if (offset > size) {
3917 throw new Error('Invalid offset!')
3918 }
3919 if ((buffer instanceof ReadBuffer) || (buffer instanceof WriteBuffer)) {
3920 this._buffer = buffer.buffer
3921 } else {
3922 this._buffer = buffer
3923 }
3924 this._size = size
3925 this._offset = offset
3926 }
3927
3934 allocate (size) {
3935 if (size < 0) {
3936 throw new Error('Invalid allocation size!')
3937 }
3938
3939 let offset = this._size
3940
3941 // Calculate a new buffer size
3942 let total = this._size + size
3943
3944 if (total <= this._buffer.length) {
3945 this._size = total
3946 return offset
3947 }
3948
3949 let data = new Uint8Array(Math.max(total, 2 * this._buffer.length))
3950 data.set(this._buffer)
3951 this._buffer = data
3952 this._size = total
3953 return offset
3954 }
3955
3962 remove (offset, size) {
3963 if ((offset + size) > this._buffer.length) {
3964 throw new Error('Invalid offset & size!')
3965 }
3966
3967 for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) {
3968 this._buffer[offset + i] = this._buffer[offset + size + i]
3969 }
3970 this._size -= size
3971 if (this._offset >= (offset + size)) {
3972 this._offset -= size
3973 } else if (this._offset >= offset) {
3974 this._offset -= this._offset - offset
3975 if (this._offset > this._size) {
3976 this._offset = this._size
3977 }
3978 }
3979 }
3980
3986 reserve (capacity) {
3987 if (capacity < 0) {
3988 throw new Error('Invalid reserve capacity!')
3989 }
3990
3991 if (capacity > this._buffer.length) {
3992 let data = new Uint8Array(Math.max(capacity, 2 * this._buffer.length))
3993 data.set(this._buffer)
3994 this._buffer = data
3995 }
3996 }
3997
4003 resize (size) {
4004 this.reserve(size)
4005 this._size = size
4006 if (this._offset > this._size) {
4007 this._offset = this._size
4008 }
4009 }
4010
4015 reset () {
4016 this._size = 0
4017 this._offset = 0
4018 }
4019}
4020
4021exports.WriteBuffer = WriteBuffer
4022)CODE";
4023
4024 // Prepare code template
4025 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
4026
4027 Write(code);
4028}

4860void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEFieldModel(const std::string& name, const std::string& type, const std::string& base, const std::string& size, const std::string& defaults)
4861{
4862 std::string code = R"CODE(
4866class FieldModel_NAME_ extends FieldModel {
4872 get fbeSize () {
4873 return _SIZE_
4874 }
4875
4882 get (defaults = _DEFAULTS_) {
4883 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
4884 return defaults
4885 }
4886
4887 return this.read_NAME_(this.fbeOffset)
4888 }
4889
4895 set (value) {
4896 console.assert(((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) <= this._buffer.size), 'Model is broken!')
4897 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
4898 return
4899 }
4900
4901 this.write_NAME_(this.fbeOffset, value)
4902 }
4903}
4904
4905exports.FieldModel_NAME_ = FieldModel_NAME_
4906)CODE";
4907
4908 // Prepare code template
4909 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_NAME_"), name);
4910 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_TYPE_"), type);
4911 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_BASE_"), base);
4912 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_SIZE_"), size);
4913 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_DEFAULTS_"), defaults);
4914 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
4915
4916 Write(code);

4919void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEFieldModelDecimal()

4925class FieldModelDecimal extends FieldModel {

4941 get (defaults = new Big(0)) {
4942 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {

4944 }
4945
4946 // Read decimal parts
4947 let low = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset)
4948 let mid = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 4)
4949 let high = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 8)
4950 let flags = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 12)
4951
4952 // Calculate decimal value
4953 let negative = (flags & 0x80000000) !== 0
4954 let scale = (flags & 0x7FFFFFFF) >> 16
4955 let result = new Big(0)
4956 result = result.add(new Big(high).mul('18446744073709551616'))
4957 result = result.add(new Big(mid).mul('4294967296'))
4958 result = result.add(new Big(low))
4959 result = result.div(Math.pow(10, scale))
4960 if (negative) {
4961 result.s = -1
4962 }
4963
4964 return result
4965 }
4966
4972 set (value) {
4973 console.assert(((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) <= this._buffer.size), 'Model is broken!')
4974 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
4975 return
4976 }
4977
4978 // Extract decimal parts
4979 let negative = value.s < 0
4980 let scale = Math.max(0, value.c.length - 1 - value.e)
4981 let number = value.mul(Math.pow(10, scale)).abs()
4982
4983 // Check for decimal scale overflow
4984 if ((scale < 0) || (scale > 28)) {
4985 // Value scale exceeds .NET Decimal limit of [0, 28]
4986 this.writeCount(this.fbeOffset, 0, this.fbeSize)
4987 return
4988 }
4989
4990 // Write unscaled value to bytes 0-11
4991 let index = 0
4992 while (number > 0) {
4993 // Check for decimal number overflow
4994 if (index > 11) {
4995 // Value too big for .NET Decimal (bit length is limited to [0, 96])
4996 this.writeCount(this.fbeOffset, 0, this.fbeSize)
4997 return
4998 }
4999 let byte = parseInt(number.mod(256))
5000 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + index, byte)
5001 number = number.div(256).round(0, 0)
5002 index++
5003 }
5004
5005 // Fill remaining bytes with zeros
5006 while (index < 12) {
5007 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + index, 0)
5008 index++
5009 }
5010
5011 // Write scale at byte 14
5012 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + 14, scale)
5013
5014 // Write signum at byte 15
5015 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + 15, (negative ? 0x80 : 0))
5016 }
5017}
5018
5019exports.FieldModelDecimal = FieldModelDecimal
5020)CODE";
5021
5022 // Prepare code template
5023 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
5024
5025 Write(code);
5026}

6415{

6427 fbeAllocationSize (value) {
6428 return this.fbeSize
6429 }
6430
6436 get fbeSize () {
6437 return _SIZE_
6438 }
6439
6445 verify () {
6446 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
6447 return Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER
6448 }

6450 return this.fbeSize
6451 }

6460 return { value: _DEFAULTS_, size: 0 }
6461 }

6464 }

6474 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {

6479 return this.fbeSize
6480 }

6497void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEFinalModelDecimal()
6498{
6499 std::string code = R"CODE(
6503class FinalModelDecimal extends FinalModel {
6510 fbeAllocationSize (value) {
6511 return this.fbeSize
6512 }
6513
6519 get fbeSize () {
6520 return 16
6521 }
6522
6528 verify () {
6529 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
6530 return Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER
6531 }
6532
6533 return this.fbeSize
6534 }
6535
6541 get () {
6542 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
6543 return { value: new Big(0), size: 0 }
6544 }
6545
6546 // Read decimal parts
6547 let low = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset)
6548 let mid = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 4)
6549 let high = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 8)
6550 let flags = this.readUInt32(this.fbeOffset + 12)
6551
6552 // Calculate decimal value
6553 let negative = (flags & 0x80000000) !== 0
6554 let scale = (flags & 0x7FFFFFFF) >> 16
6555 let result = new Big(0)
6556 result = result.add(new Big(high).mul('18446744073709551616'))
6557 result = result.add(new Big(mid).mul('4294967296'))
6558 result = result.add(new Big(low))
6559 result = result.div(Math.pow(10, scale))
6560 if (negative) {
6561 result.s = -1
6562 }
6563
6564 return { value: result, size: this.fbeSize }
6565 }
6566
6573 set (value) {
6574 console.assert(((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) <= this._buffer.size), 'Model is broken!')
6575 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
6576 return 0
6577 }
6578
6579 // Extract decimal parts
6580 let negative = value.s < 0
6581 let scale = Math.max(0, value.c.length - 1 - value.e)
6582 let number = value.mul(Math.pow(10, scale)).abs()
6583
6584 // Check for decimal scale overflow
6585 if ((scale < 0) || (scale > 28)) {
6586 // Value scale exceeds .NET Decimal limit of [0, 28]
6587 this.writeCount(this.fbeOffset, 0, this.fbeSize)
6588 return this.fbeSize
6589 }
6590
6591 // Write unscaled value to bytes 0-11
6592 let index = 0
6593 while (number > 0) {
6594 // Check for decimal number overflow
6595 if (index > 11) {
6596 // Value too big for .NET Decimal (bit length is limited to [0, 96])
6597 this.writeCount(this.fbeOffset, 0, this.fbeSize)
6598 return this.fbeSize
6599 }
6600 let byte = parseInt(number.mod(256))
6601 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + index, byte)
6602 number = number.div(256).round(0, 0)
6603 index++
6604 }
6605
6606 // Fill remaining bytes with zeros
6607 while (index < 12) {
6608 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + index, 0)
6609 index++
6610 }
6611
6612 // Write scale at byte 14
6613 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + 14, scale)
6614
6615 // Write signum at byte 15
6616 this.writeByte(this.fbeOffset + 15, (negative ? 0x80 : 0))
6617 return this.fbeSize
6618 }
6619}
6620
6621exports.FinalModelDecimal = FinalModelDecimal
6622)CODE";
6623
6624 // Prepare code template
6625 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
6626
6627 Write(code);
6628}

7730void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEReceiver()
7731{
7732 std::string code = R"CODE(
7736class Receiver {
7743 constructor (buffer = new WriteBuffer(), final = false) {
7744 this._buffer = buffer
7745 this._logging = false
7746 this._final = final
7747 }
7748
7754 get buffer () {
7755 return this._buffer
7756 }
7757
7763 get final () {
7764 return this._final
7765 }
7766
7772 get logging () {
7773 return this._logging
7774 }
7775
7781 set logging (logging) {
7782 this._logging = logging
7783 }
7784
7789 reset () {
7790 this._buffer.reset()
7791 }
7792
7800 receive (buffer, offset = 0, size = undefined) {
7801 if (size == null) {
7802 size = buffer.length
7803 }
7804
7805 console.assert(((offset + size) <= buffer.length), 'Invalid offset & size!')
7806 if ((offset + size) > buffer.length) {
7807 throw new Error('Invalid offset & size!')
7808 }
7809
7810 if (size === 0) {
7811 return
7812 }
7813
7814 if ((buffer instanceof ReadBuffer) || (buffer instanceof WriteBuffer)) {
7815 buffer = buffer.buffer
7816 }
7817
7818 // Storage buffer
7819 let offset0 = this._buffer.offset
7820 let offset1 = this._buffer.size
7821 let size1 = this._buffer.size
7822
7823 // Receive buffer
7824 let offset2 = 0
7825 let size2 = size
7826
7827 // While receive buffer is available to handle...
7828 while (offset2 < size2) {
7829 let messageBuffer = null
7830 let messageOffset = 0
7831 let messageSize = 0
7832
7833 // Try to receive message size
7834 let messageSizeCopied = false
7835 let messageSizeFound = false
7836 while (!messageSizeFound) {
7837 // Look into the storage buffer
7838 if (offset0 < size1) {
7839 let count = Math.min(size1 - offset0, 4)
7840 if (count === 4) {
7841 messageSizeCopied = true
7842 messageSizeFound = true
7843 messageSize = Receiver.readUInt32(this._buffer.buffer, this._buffer.offset + offset0)
7844 offset0 += 4
7845 break
7846 } else {
7847 // Fill remaining data from the receive buffer
7848 if (offset2 < size2) {
7849 count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, 4 - count)
7850
7851 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7852 this._buffer.allocate(count)
7853 size1 += count
7854
7855 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7856 this._buffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
7857 }
7858 offset1 += count
7859 offset2 += count
7860 continue
7861 } else {
7862 break
7863 }
7864 }
7865 }
7866
7867 // Look into the receive buffer
7868 if (offset2 < size2) {
7869 let count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, 4)
7870 if (count === 4) {
7871 messageSizeFound = true
7872 messageSize = Receiver.readUInt32(buffer, offset + offset2)
7873 offset2 += 4
7874 break
7875 } else {
7876 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7877 this._buffer.allocate(count)
7878 size1 += count
7879
7880 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7881 this._buffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
7882 }
7883 offset1 += count
7884 offset2 += count
7885 // noinspection UnnecessaryContinueJS
7886 continue
7887 }
7888 } else {
7889 break
7890 }
7891 }
7892
7893 if (!messageSizeFound) {
7894 return
7895 }
7896
7897 // Check the message full size
7898 let minSize = this._final ? (4 + 4) : (4 + 4 + 4 + 4)
7899 console.assert((messageSize >= minSize), 'Invalid receive data!')
7900 if (messageSize < minSize) {
7901 return
7902 }
7903
7904 // Try to receive message body
7905 let messageFound = false
7906 while (!messageFound) {
7907 // Look into the storage buffer
7908 if (offset0 < size1) {
7909 let count = Math.min(size1 - offset0, messageSize - 4)
7910 if (count === (messageSize - 4)) {
7911 messageFound = true
7912 messageBuffer = this._buffer.buffer
7913 messageOffset = offset0 - 4
7914 offset0 += messageSize - 4
7915 break
7916 } else {
7917 // Fill remaining data from the receive buffer
7918 if (offset2 < size2) {
7919 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
7920 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
7921 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7922 this._buffer.allocate(4)
7923 size1 += 4
7924
7925 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._buffer.buffer, this._buffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
7926 offset0 += 4
7927 offset1 += 4
7928
7929 messageSizeCopied = true
7930 }
7931
7932 count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, messageSize - 4 - count)
7933
7934 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7935 this._buffer.allocate(count)
7936 size1 += count
7937
7938 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7939 this._buffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
7940 }
7941 offset1 += count
7942 offset2 += count
7943 continue
7944 } else {
7945 break
7946 }
7947 }
7948 }
7949
7950 // Look into the receive buffer
7951 if (offset2 < size2) {
7952 let count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, messageSize - 4)
7953 if (!messageSizeCopied && (count === (messageSize - 4))) {
7954 messageFound = true
7955 messageBuffer = buffer
7956 messageOffset = offset + offset2 - 4
7957 offset2 += messageSize - 4
7958 break
7959 } else {
7960 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
7961 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
7962 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7963 this._buffer.allocate(4)
7964 size1 += 4
7965
7966 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._buffer.buffer, this._buffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
7967 offset0 += 4
7968 offset1 += 4
7969
7970 messageSizeCopied = true
7971 }
7972
7973 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7974 this._buffer.allocate(count)
7975 size1 += count
7976
7977 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7978 this._buffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
7979 }
7980 offset1 += count
7981 offset2 += count
7982 // noinspection UnnecessaryContinueJS
7983 continue
7984 }
7985 } else {
7986 break
7987 }
7988 }
7989
7990 if (!messageFound) {
7991 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
7992 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
7993 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
7994 this._buffer.allocate(4)
7995 size1 += 4
7996
7997 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._buffer.buffer, this._buffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
7998 offset0 += 4
7999 offset1 += 4
8000
8001 messageSizeCopied = true
8002 }
8003 return
8004 }
8005
8006 // noinspection JSUnusedLocalSymbols
8007 let fbeStructSize // eslint-disable-line
8008 let fbeStructType
8009
8010 // Read the message parameters
8011 if (this._final) {
8012 fbeStructSize = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset)
8013 fbeStructType = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + 4)
8014 } else {
8015 let fbeStructOffset = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + 4)
8016 // noinspection JSUnusedLocalSymbols
8017 fbeStructSize = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + fbeStructOffset) // eslint-disable-line
8018 fbeStructType = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + fbeStructOffset + 4)
8019 }
8020
8021 // Handle the message
8022 this.onReceive(fbeStructType, messageBuffer, messageOffset, messageSize)
8023
8024 // Reset the storage buffer
8025 this._buffer.reset()
8026
8027 // Refresh the storage buffer
8028 offset0 = this._buffer.offset
8029 offset1 = this._buffer.size
8030 size1 = this._buffer.size
8031 }
8032 }
8033
8043 onReceive (type, buffer, offset, size) {
8044 console.assert(true, 'Abstract method call!')
8045 debugger // eslint-disable-line
8046 return false
8047 }
8048
8054 onReceiveLog (message) {}
8055
8061 set onReceiveLogHandler (handler) { // eslint-disable-line
8062 this.onReceiveLog = handler
8063 }
8064
8065 // Buffer I/O methods
8066
8073 static checkOffset (buffer, offset, size) {
8074 if (((offset % 1) !== 0) || (offset < 0)) {
8075 throw new RangeError('Invalid offset!')
8076 }
8077 if ((offset + size) > buffer.length) {
8078 throw new RangeError('Out of bounds!')
8079 }
8080 }
8081
8091 static checkValue (buffer, offset, size, value, min, max) {
8092 this.checkOffset(buffer, offset, size)
8093 if ((value < min) || (value > max)) {
8094 throw new RangeError('Value is out of bounds!')
8095 }
8096 }
8097
8105 static readUInt32 (buffer, offset) {
8106 offset = offset >>> 0
8107 Receiver.checkOffset(buffer, offset, 4)
8108 return (
8109 (buffer[offset + 0] << 0) |
8110 (buffer[offset + 1] << 8) |
8111 (buffer[offset + 2] << 16)) +
8112 (buffer[offset + 3] * 0x1000000)
8113 }
8114
8122 static writeUInt32 (buffer, offset, value) {
8123 value = +value
8124 Receiver.checkValue(buffer, offset, 4, value, 0, 0xFFFFFFFF)
8125 buffer[offset + 3] = (value >>> 24)
8126 buffer[offset + 2] = (value >>> 16)
8127 buffer[offset + 1] = (value >>> 8)
8128 buffer[offset + 0] = (value & 0xFF)
8129 }
8130}
8131
8132exports.Receiver = Receiver
8133)CODE";
8134
8135 // Prepare code template
8136 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
8137
8138 Write(code);
8139}

8141void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEClient()
8142{
8143 std::string code = R"CODE(
8147class Client {
8155 constructor (sendBuffer = new WriteBuffer(), receiveBuffer = new WriteBuffer(), final = false) {
8156 this._sendBuffer = sendBuffer
8157 this._receiveBuffer = receiveBuffer
8158 this._logging = false
8159 this._final = final
8160 }
8161
8167 get sendBuffer () {
8168 return this._sendBuffer
8169 }
8170
8176 get receiveBuffer () {
8177 return this._receiveBuffer
8178 }
8179
8185 get final () {
8186 return this._final
8187 }
8188
8194 get logging () {
8195 return this._logging
8196 }
8197
8203 set logging (logging) {
8204 this._logging = logging
8205 }
8206
8211 reset () {
8212 this._sendBuffer.reset()
8213 this._receiveBuffer.reset()
8214 }
8215
8224 sendSerialized (serialized) {
8225 console.assert((serialized > 0), 'Invalid size of the serialized buffer!')
8226 if (serialized <= 0) {
8227 return 0
8228 }
8229
8230 // Shift the send buffer
8231 this._sendBuffer.shift(serialized)
8232
8233 // Send the value
8234 let sent = this.onSend(this._sendBuffer.buffer, 0, this._sendBuffer.size)
8235 this._sendBuffer.remove(0, sent)
8236 return sent
8237 }
8238

8247 console.assert(true, 'Abstract method call!')
8248 debugger // eslint-disable-line
8249 return 0
8250 }
8251

8258

8265 this.onSend = handler
8266 }
8267
8273 set onSendLogHandler (handler) { // eslint-disable-line
8274 this.onSendLog = handler

8276
8284 receive (buffer, offset = 0, size = undefined) {
8285 if (size == null) {
8286 size = buffer.length
8287 }
8288
8289 console.assert(((offset + size) <= buffer.length), 'Invalid offset & size!')
8290 if ((offset + size) > buffer.length) {
8291 throw new Error('Invalid offset & size!')
8292 }
8293
8294 if (size === 0) {
8295 return
8296 }
8297
8298 if ((buffer instanceof ReadBuffer) || (buffer instanceof WriteBuffer)) {
8299 buffer = buffer.buffer
8300 }
8301
8302 // Storage buffer
8303 let offset0 = this._receiveBuffer.offset
8304 let offset1 = this._receiveBuffer.size
8305 let size1 = this._receiveBuffer.size
8306
8307 // Receive buffer
8308 let offset2 = 0
8309 let size2 = size
8310
8311 // While receive buffer is available to handle...
8312 while (offset2 < size2) {
8313 let messageBuffer = null
8314 let messageOffset = 0
8315 let messageSize = 0
8316
8317 // Try to receive message size
8318 let messageSizeCopied = false
8319 let messageSizeFound = false
8320 while (!messageSizeFound) {
8321 // Look into the storage buffer
8322 if (offset0 < size1) {
8323 let count = Math.min(size1 - offset0, 4)
8324 if (count === 4) {
8325 messageSizeCopied = true
8326 messageSizeFound = true
8327 messageSize = Receiver.readUInt32(this._receiveBuffer.buffer, this._receiveBuffer.offset + offset0)
8328 offset0 += 4
8329 break
8330 } else {
8331 // Fill remaining data from the receive buffer
8332 if (offset2 < size2) {
8333 count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, 4 - count)
8334
8335 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8336 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(count)
8337 size1 += count
8338
8339 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8340 this._receiveBuffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
8341 }
8342 offset1 += count
8343 offset2 += count
8344 continue
8345 } else {
8346 break
8347 }
8348 }
8349 }
8350
8351 // Look into the receive buffer
8352 if (offset2 < size2) {
8353 let count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, 4)
8354 if (count === 4) {
8355 messageSizeFound = true
8356 messageSize = Receiver.readUInt32(buffer, offset + offset2)
8357 offset2 += 4
8358 break
8359 } else {
8360 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8361 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(count)
8362 size1 += count
8363
8364 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8365 this._receiveBuffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
8366 }
8367 offset1 += count
8368 offset2 += count
8369 // noinspection UnnecessaryContinueJS
8370 continue
8371 }
8372 } else {
8373 break
8374 }
8375 }
8376
8377 if (!messageSizeFound) {
8378 return
8379 }
8380
8381 // Check the message full size
8382 let minSize = this._final ? (4 + 4) : (4 + 4 + 4 + 4)
8383 console.assert((messageSize >= minSize), 'Invalid receive data!')
8384 if (messageSize < minSize) {
8385 return
8386 }
8387
8388 // Try to receive message body
8389 let messageFound = false
8390 while (!messageFound) {
8391 // Look into the storage buffer
8392 if (offset0 < size1) {
8393 let count = Math.min(size1 - offset0, messageSize - 4)
8394 if (count === (messageSize - 4)) {
8395 messageFound = true
8396 messageBuffer = this._receiveBuffer.buffer
8397 messageOffset = offset0 - 4
8398 offset0 += messageSize - 4
8399 break
8400 } else {
8401 // Fill remaining data from the receive buffer
8402 if (offset2 < size2) {
8403 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
8404 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
8405 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8406 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(4)
8407 size1 += 4
8408
8409 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._receiveBuffer.buffer, this._receiveBuffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
8410 offset0 += 4
8411 offset1 += 4
8412
8413 messageSizeCopied = true
8414 }
8415
8416 count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, messageSize - 4 - count)
8417
8418 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8419 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(count)
8420 size1 += count
8421
8422 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8423 this._receiveBuffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
8424 }
8425 offset1 += count
8426 offset2 += count
8427 continue
8428 } else {
8429 break
8430 }
8431 }
8432 }
8433
8434 // Look into the receive buffer
8435 if (offset2 < size2) {
8436 let count = Math.min(size2 - offset2, messageSize - 4)
8437 if (!messageSizeCopied && (count === (messageSize - 4))) {
8438 messageFound = true
8439 messageBuffer = buffer
8440 messageOffset = offset + offset2 - 4
8441 offset2 += messageSize - 4
8442 break
8443 } else {
8444 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
8445 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
8446 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8447 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(4)
8448 size1 += 4
8449
8450 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._receiveBuffer.buffer, this._receiveBuffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
8451 offset0 += 4
8452 offset1 += 4
8453
8454 messageSizeCopied = true
8455 }
8456
8457 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8458 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(count)
8459 size1 += count
8460
8461 for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8462 this._receiveBuffer.buffer[offset1 + i] = buffer[offset + offset2 + i]
8463 }
8464 offset1 += count
8465 offset2 += count
8466 // noinspection UnnecessaryContinueJS
8467 continue
8468 }
8469 } else {
8470 break
8471 }
8472 }
8473
8474 if (!messageFound) {
8475 // Copy message size into the storage buffer
8476 if (!messageSizeCopied) {
8477 // Allocate and refresh the storage buffer
8478 this._receiveBuffer.allocate(4)
8479 size1 += 4
8480
8481 Receiver.writeUInt32(this._receiveBuffer.buffer, this._receiveBuffer.offset + offset0, messageSize)
8482 offset0 += 4
8483 offset1 += 4
8484
8485 messageSizeCopied = true
8486 }
8487 return
8488 }
8489
8490 // noinspection JSUnusedLocalSymbols
8491 let fbeStructSize // eslint-disable-line
8492 let fbeStructType
8493
8494 // Read the message parameters
8495 if (this._final) {
8496 fbeStructSize = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset)
8497 fbeStructType = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + 4)
8498 } else {
8499 let fbeStructOffset = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + 4)
8500 // noinspection JSUnusedLocalSymbols
8501 fbeStructSize = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + fbeStructOffset) // eslint-disable-line
8502 fbeStructType = Receiver.readUInt32(messageBuffer, messageOffset + fbeStructOffset + 4)
8503 }
8504
8505 // Handle the message
8506 this.onReceive(fbeStructType, messageBuffer, messageOffset, messageSize)
8507
8508 // Reset the storage buffer
8509 this._receiveBuffer.reset()
8510
8511 // Refresh the storage buffer
8512 offset0 = this._receiveBuffer.offset
8513 offset1 = this._receiveBuffer.size
8514 size1 = this._receiveBuffer.size
8515 }
8516 }
8517
8527 onReceive (type, buffer, offset, size) {
8528 console.assert(true, 'Abstract method call!')
8529 debugger // eslint-disable-line
8530 return false
8531 }
8532
8538 onReceiveLog (message) {}
8539
8545 set onReceiveLogHandler (handler) { // eslint-disable-line
8546 this.onReceiveLog = handler
8547 }
8548
8549 // Buffer I/O methods
8550
8557 static checkOffset (buffer, offset, size) {
8558 if (((offset % 1) !== 0) || (offset < 0)) {
8559 throw new RangeError('Invalid offset!')
8560 }
8561 if ((offset + size) > buffer.length) {
8562 throw new RangeError('Out of bounds!')

8609 buffer[offset + 3] = (value >>> 24)

8625void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFBEJson()
8626{
8627 std::string code = R"CODE(
8633let MapToObject = function (map) {
8634 let obj = {}
8635 map.forEach((value, key) => { obj[key] = value })
8636 return obj
8637}
8638
8639exports.MapToObject = MapToObject
8640
8646let ObjectToMap = function (obj) {
8647 let map = new Map()
8648 Object.keys(obj).forEach(key => { map.set(key, obj[key]) })
8649 return map
8650}
8651
8652exports.ObjectToMap = ObjectToMap
8653)CODE";
8654
