8660
8661void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateImports(const std::shared_ptr<Package>& p)
8662{
8663 // Generate common import
8664 WriteLine();
8665 WriteLineIndent("const util = require('util')");
8666 WriteLine();
8667 WriteLineIndent("const big = require('./big')");
8668 WriteLineIndent("const int64 = require('./int64')");
8669 WriteLineIndent("const uuid = require('./uuid')");
8670 WriteLine();
8671 WriteLineIndent("const Big = big.Big // eslint-disable-line");
8672 WriteLineIndent("const Int64 = int64.Int64 // eslint-disable-line");
8673 WriteLineIndent("const UInt64 = int64.UInt64 // eslint-disable-line");
8674 WriteLineIndent("const UUID = uuid.UUID // eslint-disable-line");
8675
8676 // Generate FBE import
8677 WriteLine();
8678 WriteLineIndent("const fbe = require('./fbe')");
8679
8680 // Generate packages import
8681 if (p->import)
8682 for (const auto& import : p->import->imports)
8683 WriteLineIndent("const " + *import + " = require('./" + *import + "')");
8684}
8685
8686void GeneratorJavaScript::GeneratePackage(const std::shared_ptr<Package>& p)
8687{
8688 CppCommon::Path output = _output;
8689
8690 // Create package path
8691 CppCommon::Directory::CreateTree(output);
8692
8693 // Generate common files
8694 GenerateBig(output);
8695 GenerateInt64(output);
8696 GenerateUUID(output);
8697 GenerateIEEE754(output);
8698 GenerateUTF8(output);
8699 GenerateFBE(output);
8700
8701 // Generate the output file
8702 output /= *p->name + ".js";
8703 WriteBegin();
8704
8705 // Generate package header
8706 GenerateHeader(CppCommon::Path(_input).filename().string());
8707
8708 // Generate eslint deflations
8709 WriteLine();
8710 WriteLineIndent("/* eslint-disable prefer-const,no-loss-of-precision */");
8711 WriteLineIndent("'use strict'");
8712
8713 // Generate package imports
8714 GenerateImports(p);
8715
8716 // Generate namespace
8717 if (p->body)
8718 {
8719 // Generate child enums
8720 for (const auto& child_e : p->body->enums)
8721 GenerateEnum(child_e);
8722
8723 // Generate child flags
8724 for (const auto& child_f : p->body->flags)
8725 GenerateFlags(child_f);
8726
8727 // Generate child structs
8728 for (const auto& child_s : p->body->structs)
8729 GenerateStruct(child_s);
8730 }
8731
8732 // Generate protocol
8733 if (Proto())
8734 {
8735 // Generate protocol version
8736 GenerateProtocolVersion(p);
8737
8738 // Generate sender & receiver
8739 GenerateSender(p, false);
8740 GenerateReceiver(p, false);
8741 GenerateProxy(p, false);
8742 GenerateClient(p, false);
8743 if (Final())
8744 {
8745 GenerateSender(p, true);
8746 GenerateReceiver(p, true);
8747 GenerateClient(p, true);
8748 }
8749 }
8750
8751 // Generate package footer
8752 GenerateFooter();
8753
8754 // Store the output file
8755 WriteEnd();
8756 Store(output);
8757}
8758
8759void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateEnum(const std::shared_ptr<EnumType>& e)
8760{
8761 // Generate enum begin
8762 WriteLine();
8763 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8764 WriteLineIndent(" * " + *e->name + " enum");
8765 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8766 WriteLineIndent("class " + *e->name + " {");
8767 Indent(1);
8768
8769 std::string enum_type = (e->base && !e->base->empty()) ? *e->base : "int32";
8770
8771 // Javascript enums are limited to 32-bit integer numbers
8772 if (enum_type == "int64")
8773 enum_type = "int32";
8774 else if (enum_type == "uint64")
8775 enum_type = "uint32";
8776
8777 // Generate enum constructor
8778 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8779 WriteLineIndent(" * Initialize enum with a given value");
8780 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {" + *e->name + "|number|Int64|UInt64=} value Enum value, defaults is 0");
8781 WriteLineIndent(" * @constructor");
8782 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8783 WriteLineIndent("constructor (value = 0) {");
8784 Indent(1);
8785 WriteLineIndent("if (value instanceof " + *e->name + ") {");
8786 Indent(1);
8787 WriteLineIndent("this.value = value.value");
8788 Indent(-1);
8789 WriteLineIndent("} else {");
8790 Indent(1);
8791 WriteLineIndent("this.value = value");
8792 Indent(-1);
8793 WriteLineIndent("}");
8794 Indent(-1);
8795 WriteLineIndent("}");
8796
8797 // Generate enum eq() method
8798 WriteLine();
8799 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8800 WriteLineIndent(" * Is this enum equal to other one?");
8801 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *e->name + "}");
8802 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!" + *e->name + "} other Other enum");
8803 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {boolean} Equal result");
8804 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8805 WriteLineIndent("eq (other) {");
8806 Indent(1);
8807 WriteLineIndent("if (!(other instanceof " + *e->name + ")) {");
8808 Indent(1);
8809 WriteLineIndent("throw new TypeError('Instance of " + *e->name + " is required!')");
8810 Indent(-1);
8811 WriteLineIndent("}");
8812 WriteLineIndent("return this.value === other.value");
8813 Indent(-1);
8814 WriteLineIndent("}");
8815
8816 // Generate enum valueOf() method
8817 WriteLine();
8818 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8819 WriteLineIndent(" * Get enum value");
8820 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *e->name + "}");
8821 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!number|!Int64|!UInt64} Enum value");
8822 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8823 WriteLineIndent("valueOf () {");
8824 Indent(1);
8825 WriteLineIndent("return this.value");
8826 Indent(-1);
8827 WriteLineIndent("}");
8828
8829 // Generate enum toString() method
8830 WriteLine();
8831 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8832 WriteLineIndent(" * Convert enum to string");
8833 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *e->name + "}");
8834 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!string} Enum value string");
8835 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8836 WriteLineIndent("toString () {");
8837 Indent(1);
8838 if (e->body && !e->body->values.empty())
8839 {
8840 for (auto it = e->body->values.begin(); it != e->body->values.end(); ++it)
8841 {
8842 WriteLineIndent("if (this.value === " + *e->name + "." + *(*it)->name + ".value) {");
8843 Indent(1);
8844 WriteLineIndent("return '" + *(*it)->name + "'");
8845 Indent(-1);
8846 WriteLineIndent("}");
8847 }
8848 WriteLineIndent("return '<unknown>'");
8849 }
8850 else
8851 WriteLineIndent("return '<empty>'");
8852 Indent(-1);
8853 WriteLineIndent("}");
8854
8855 // Generate enum [util.inspect.custom]() method
8856 WriteLine();
8857 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8858 WriteLineIndent(" * Inspect enum");
8859 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *e->name + "}");
8860 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!string} Enum value string");
8861 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8862 WriteLineIndent("[util.inspect.custom] () {");
8863 Indent(1);
8864 WriteLineIndent("return this.toString()");
8865 Indent(-1);
8866 WriteLineIndent("}");
8867
8868 // Generate enum toJSON() method
8869 WriteLine();
8870 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8871 WriteLineIndent(" * Convert enum to JSON");
8872 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *e->name + "}");
8873 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!number} Enum value for JSON");
8874 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8875 WriteLineIndent("toJSON () {");
8876 Indent(1);
8877 WriteLineIndent("return this.value");
8878 Indent(-1);
8879 WriteLineIndent("}");
8880
8881 // Generate enum fromObject() method
8882 WriteLine();
8883 WriteLineIndent("/**");
8884 WriteLineIndent(" * Create enum from object value");
8885 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!number} other Object value");
8886 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!" + *e->name + "} Created enum");
8887 WriteLineIndent(" */");
8888 WriteLineIndent("static fromObject (other) {");
8889 Indent(1);
8890 WriteLineIndent("return new " + *e->name + "(other)");
8891 Indent(-1);
8892 WriteLineIndent("}");
8893
8894 // Generate enum end
8895 Indent(-1);
8896 WriteLineIndent("}");
8897
8898 // Generate enum values
8899 if (e->body && !e->body->values.empty())
8900 {
8901 WriteLine();
8902 int index = 0;
8903 std::string last = ConvertEnumConstant(*e->name, "int32", "0");
8904 for (const auto& value : e->body->values)
8905 {
8906 WriteLineIndent("// noinspection PointlessArithmeticExpressionJS");
8907 WriteIndent(*e->name + "." + *value->name + " = new " + *e->name + "(");
8908 if (value->value)
8909 {
8910 if (value->value->constant && !value->value->constant->empty())
8911 {
8912 index = 0;
8913 last = ConvertEnumConstant(*e->name, enum_type, *value->value->constant);
8914 Write(last + " + " + std::to_string(index++));
8915 }
8916 else if (value->value->reference && !value->value->reference->empty())
8917 {
8918 index = 0;
8919 last = ConvertEnumConstant(*e->name, "", *value->value->reference);
8920 Write(last);
8921 }
8922 }
8923 else
8924 Write(last + " + " + std::to_string(index++));
8925 Write(")");
8926 WriteLine();
8927 }
8928 }
8929
8930 // Generate enum exports
8931 WriteLine();
8932 WriteLineIndent("exports." + *e->name + " = " + *e->name);
8933
8934 // Generate enum field model
8935 GenerateEnumFieldModel(e);
8936
8937 // Generate enum final model
8938 if (Final())
8939 GenerateEnumFinalModel(e);
8940}
8941
8942void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateEnumFieldModel(const std::shared_ptr<EnumType>& e)
8943{
8944 std::string code = R"CODE(
8948class FieldModel_ENUM_NAME_ extends fbe.FieldModel {
8954 get fbeSize () {
8955 return _ENUM_SIZE_
8956 }
8957
8964 get (defaults = new _ENUM_NAME_()) {
8965 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
8966 return defaults
8967 }
8968
8969 return new _ENUM_NAME_(this.read_ENUM_TYPE_(this.fbeOffset)_ENUM_READ_SUFFIX_)
8970 }
8971
8977 set (value) {
8978 console.assert(((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) <= this._buffer.size), 'Model is broken!')
8979 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
8980 return
8981 }
8982
8983 this.write_ENUM_TYPE_(this.fbeOffset, _ENUM_WRITE_PREFIX_value.value_ENUM_WRITE_SUFFIX_)
8984 }
8985}
8986
8987exports.FieldModel_ENUM_NAME_ = FieldModel_ENUM_NAME_
8988)CODE";
8989
8990 std::string enum_type = (e->base && !e->base->empty()) ? *e->base : "int32";
8991 std::string enum_read_suffix = "";
8992 std::string enum_write_prefix = "";
8993 std::string enum_write_suffix = "";
8994
8995 // Javascript enums are limited to 32-bit integer numbers
8996 if (enum_type == "int64")
8997 {
8998 enum_read_suffix = ".toNumber()";
8999 enum_write_prefix = "Int64.fromNumber(";
9000 enum_write_suffix = ")";
9001 }
9002 else if (enum_type == "uint64")
9003 {
9004 enum_read_suffix = ".toNumber()";
9005 enum_write_prefix = "UInt64.fromNumber(";
9006 enum_write_suffix = ")";
9007 }
9008
9009 // Prepare code template
9010 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_NAME_"), *e->name);
9011 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_TYPE_"), ConvertEnumType(enum_type));
9012 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_SIZE_"), ConvertEnumSize(enum_type));
9013 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_READ_SUFFIX_"), enum_read_suffix);
9014 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_WRITE_PREFIX_"), enum_write_prefix);
9015 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_WRITE_SUFFIX_"), enum_write_suffix);
9016 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
9017
9018 Write(code);
9019}
9020
9021void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateEnumFinalModel(const std::shared_ptr<EnumType>& e)
9022{
9023 std::string code = R"CODE(
9027class FinalModel_ENUM_NAME_ extends fbe.FinalModel {
9034 fbeAllocationSize (value) {
9035 return this.fbeSize
9036 }
9037
9043 get fbeSize () {
9044 return _ENUM_SIZE_
9045 }
9046
9052 verify () {
9053 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
9054 return Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER
9055 }
9056
9057 return this.fbeSize
9058 }
9059
9065 get () {
9066 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
9067 return { value: new _ENUM_NAME_(), size: 0 }
9068 }
9069
9070 return { value: new _ENUM_NAME_(this.read_ENUM_TYPE_(this.fbeOffset)_ENUM_READ_SUFFIX_), size: this.fbeSize }
9071 }
9072
9079 set (value) {
9080 console.assert(((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) <= this._buffer.size), 'Model is broken!')
9081 if ((this._buffer.offset + this.fbeOffset + this.fbeSize) > this._buffer.size) {
9082 return 0
9083 }
9084
9085 this.write_ENUM_TYPE_(this.fbeOffset, _ENUM_WRITE_PREFIX_value.value_ENUM_WRITE_SUFFIX_)
9086 return this.fbeSize
9087 }
9088}
9089
9090exports.FinalModel_ENUM_NAME_ = FinalModel_ENUM_NAME_
9091)CODE";
9092
9093 std::string enum_type = (e->base && !e->base->empty()) ? *e->base : "int32";
9094 std::string enum_read_suffix = "";
9095 std::string enum_write_prefix = "";
9096 std::string enum_write_suffix = "";
9097
9098 // Javascript enums are limited to 32-bit integer numbers
9099 if (enum_type == "int64")
9100 {
9101 enum_read_suffix = ".toNumber()";
9102 enum_write_prefix = "Int64.fromNumber(";
9103 enum_write_suffix = ")";
9104 }
9105 else if (enum_type == "uint64")
9106 {
9107 enum_read_suffix = ".toNumber()";
9108 enum_write_prefix = "UInt64.fromNumber(";
9109 enum_write_suffix = ")";
9110 }
9111
9112 // Prepare code template
9113 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_NAME_"), *e->name);
9114 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_TYPE_"), ConvertEnumType(enum_type));
9115 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_SIZE_"), ConvertEnumSize(enum_type));
9116 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_READ_SUFFIX_"), enum_read_suffix);
9117 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_WRITE_PREFIX_"), enum_write_prefix);
9118 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("_ENUM_WRITE_SUFFIX_"), enum_write_suffix);
9119 code = std::regex_replace(code, std::regex("\n"), EndLine());
9120
9121 Write(code);
9122}
9123
9124void GeneratorJavaScript::GenerateFlags(const std::shared_ptr<FlagsType>& f)
9125{
9126 // Generate flags begin
9127 WriteLine();
9128 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9129 WriteLineIndent(" * " + *f->name + " flags");
9130 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9131 WriteLineIndent("class " + *f->name + " {");
9132 Indent(1);
9133
9134 std::string flags_type = (f->base && !f->base->empty()) ? *f->base : "int32";
9135
9136 // Javascript flags are limited to 32-bit integer numbers
9137 if (flags_type == "int64")
9138 flags_type = "int32";
9139 else if (flags_type == "uint64")
9140 flags_type = "uint32";
9141
9142 // Generate flags constructor
9143 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9144 WriteLineIndent(" * Initialize flags with a given value");
9145 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {" + *f->name + "|number|Int64|UInt64=} value Flags value, defaults is 0");
9146 WriteLineIndent(" * @constructor");
9147 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9148 WriteLineIndent("constructor (value = 0) {");
9149 Indent(1);
9150 WriteLineIndent("if (value instanceof " + *f->name + ") {");
9151 Indent(1);
9152 WriteLineIndent("this.value = value.value");
9153 Indent(-1);
9154 WriteLineIndent("} else {");
9155 Indent(1);
9156 WriteLineIndent("this.value = value");
9157 Indent(-1);
9158 WriteLineIndent("}");
9159 Indent(-1);
9160 WriteLineIndent("}");
9161
9162 // Generate flags hasFlags() method
9163 WriteLine();
9164 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9165 WriteLineIndent(" * Check for the given flags set state");
9166 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9167 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!" + *f->name + "|!number|!Int64|!UInt64} flags Flags");
9168 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!boolean} Flags set state");
9169 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9170 WriteLineIndent("hasFlags (flags) {");
9171 Indent(1);
9172 WriteLineIndent("if (flags instanceof " + *f->name + ") {");
9173 Indent(1);
9174 WriteLineIndent("flags = flags.value");
9175 Indent(-1);
9176 WriteLineIndent("}");
9177 WriteLineIndent("return ((this.value & flags) !== 0) && ((this.value & flags) === flags)");
9178 Indent(-1);
9179 WriteLineIndent("}");
9180
9181 // Generate flags setFlags() method
9182 WriteLine();
9183 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9184 WriteLineIndent(" * Set the given flags");
9185 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9186 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!" + *f->name + "|!number|!Int64|!UInt64} flags Flags");
9187 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9188 WriteLineIndent("setFlags (flags) {");
9189 Indent(1);
9190 WriteLineIndent("if (flags instanceof " + *f->name + ") {");
9191 Indent(1);
9192 WriteLineIndent("flags = flags.value");
9193 Indent(-1);
9194 WriteLineIndent("}");
9195 WriteLineIndent("this.value |= flags");
9196 WriteLineIndent("return this");
9197 Indent(-1);
9198 WriteLineIndent("}");
9199
9200 // Generate flags removeFlags() method
9201 WriteLine();
9202 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9203 WriteLineIndent(" * Remove the given flags");
9204 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9205 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!" + *f->name + "|!number|!Int64|!UInt64} flags Flags");
9206 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9207 WriteLineIndent("removeFlags (flags) {");
9208 Indent(1);
9209 WriteLineIndent("if (flags instanceof " + *f->name + ") {");
9210 Indent(1);
9211 WriteLineIndent("flags = flags.value");
9212 Indent(-1);
9213 WriteLineIndent("}");
9214 WriteLineIndent("this.value &= ~flags");
9215 WriteLineIndent("return this");
9216 Indent(-1);
9217 WriteLineIndent("}");
9218
9219 // Generate flags eq() method
9220 WriteLine();
9221 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9222 WriteLineIndent(" * Is this flags equal to other one?");
9223 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9224 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!" + *f->name + "} other Other flags");
9225 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {boolean} Equal result");
9226 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9227 WriteLineIndent("eq (other) {");
9228 Indent(1);
9229 WriteLineIndent("if (!(other instanceof " + *f->name + ")) {");
9230 Indent(1);
9231 WriteLineIndent("throw new TypeError('Instance of " + *f->name + " is required!')");
9232 Indent(-1);
9233 WriteLineIndent("}");
9234 WriteLineIndent("return this.value === other.value");
9235 Indent(-1);
9236 WriteLineIndent("}");
9237
9238 // Generate flags valueOf() method
9239 WriteLine();
9240 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9241 WriteLineIndent(" * Get flags value");
9242 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9243 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!number|!Int64|!UInt64} Flags value");
9244 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9245 WriteLineIndent("valueOf () {");
9246 Indent(1);
9247 WriteLineIndent("return this.value");
9248 Indent(-1);
9249 WriteLineIndent("}");
9250
9251 // Generate flags toString() method
9252 WriteLine();
9253 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9254 WriteLineIndent(" * Convert flags to string");
9255 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9256 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!string} Flags value string");
9257 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9258 WriteLineIndent("toString () {");
9259 Indent(1);
9260 WriteLineIndent("let result = ''");
9261 if (f->body && !f->body->values.empty())
9262 {
9263 WriteLineIndent("let first = true");
9264 for (auto it = f->body->values.begin(); it != f->body->values.end(); ++it)
9265 {
9266 WriteLineIndent("if ((this.value & " + *f->name + "." + *(*it)->name + ".value) && ((this.value & " + *f->name + "." + *(*it)->name + ".value) === " + *f->name + "." + *(*it)->name + ".value)) {");
9267 Indent(1);
9268 WriteLineIndent("result += (first ? '' : '|') + '" + *(*it)->name + "'");
9269 WriteLineIndent("// noinspection JSUnusedAssignment");
9270 WriteLineIndent("first = false");
9271 Indent(-1);
9272 WriteLineIndent("}");
9273 }
9274 }
9275 WriteLineIndent("return result");
9276 Indent(-1);
9277 WriteLineIndent("}");
9278
9279 // Generate flags [util.inspect.custom]() method
9280 WriteLine();
9281 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9282 WriteLineIndent(" * Inspect flags");
9283 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9284 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!string} Flags value string");
9285 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9286 WriteLineIndent("[util.inspect.custom] () {");
9287 Indent(1);
9288 WriteLineIndent("return this.toString()");
9289 Indent(-1);
9290 WriteLineIndent("}");
9291
9292 // Generate flags toJSON() method
9293 WriteLine();
9294 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9295 WriteLineIndent(" * Convert flags to JSON");
9296 WriteLineIndent(" * @this {!" + *f->name + "}");
9297 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!number} Flags value for JSON");
9298 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9299 WriteLineIndent("toJSON () {");
9300 Indent(1);
9301 WriteLineIndent("return this.value");
9302 Indent(-1);
9303 WriteLineIndent("}");
9304
9305 // Generate flags fromFlags() method
9306 WriteLine();
9307 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9308 WriteLineIndent(" * Create flags from number flags representation");
9309 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!number} flags Number flags representation");
9310 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!" + *f->name + "} Created flags");
9311 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9312 WriteLineIndent("static fromFlags (flags) {");
9313 Indent(1);
9314 WriteLineIndent("return new " + *f->name + "(flags)");
9315 Indent(-1);
9316 WriteLineIndent("}");
9317
9318 // Generate flags fromObject() method
9319 WriteLine();
9320 WriteLineIndent("/**");
9321 WriteLineIndent(" * Create flags from object value");
9322 WriteLineIndent(" * @param {!number} other Object value");
9323 WriteLineIndent(" * @returns {!" + *f->name + "} Created flags");
9324 WriteLineIndent(" */");
9325 WriteLineIndent("static fromObject (other) {");
9326 Indent(1);
9327 WriteLineIndent("return new " + *f->name + "(other)");
9328 Indent(-1);
9329 WriteLineIndent("}");
9330
9331 // Generate flags end
9332 Indent(-1);
9333 WriteLineIndent("}");
9334
9335 // Generate flags values
9336 if (f->body && !f->body->values.empty())
9337 {
9338 WriteLine();
9339 for (const auto& value : f->body->values)
9340 {
9341 WriteLineIndent("// noinspection PointlessArithmeticExpressionJS");
9342 WriteIndent(*f->name + "." + *value->name + " = new " + *f->name + "(");
9343 if (value->value)
9344 {
9345 if (value->value->constant && !value->value->constant->empty())
9346 Write(ConvertEnumConstant(*f->name, flags_type, *value->value->constant));
9347 else if (value->value->reference && !value->value->reference->empty())
9348 Write(ConvertEnumConstant(*f->name, "", *value->value->reference));
9349 }
9350 Write(")");
9351 WriteLine();
9352 }
9353 }
9354
9355 // Generate flags exports
9356 WriteLine();
9357 WriteLineIndent("exports." + *f->name + " = " + *f->name);
9358
9359 // Generate flags field model
9360 GenerateFlagsFieldModel(f);
9361
9362 // Generate flags final model
9363 if (Final())
9364 GenerateFlagsFinalModel(f);
9365}

9395 }
9396
